31   "no use strict";
32   !(function(window) {
33   if (typeof window.window != "undefined" && window.document)
34       return;
35   if (window.require && window.define)
36       return;
37   
38   if (!window.console) {
39       window.console = function() {
40           var msgs = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments, 0);
41           postMessage({type: "log", data: msgs});
42       };
43       window.console.error =
44       window.console.warn = 
45       window.console.log =
46       window.console.trace = window.console;
47   }
48   window.window = window;
49   window.ace = window;

51   window.onerror = function(message, file, line, col, err) {
52       postMessage({type: "error", data: {
53           message: message,
54           data: err.data,
55           file: file,
56           line: line, 
57           col: col,
58           stack: err.stack
59       }});
60   };
61   
62   window.normalizeModule = function(parentId, moduleName) {
63       // normalize plugin requires
64       if (moduleName.indexOf("!") !== -1) {
65           var chunks = moduleName.split("!");
66           return window.normalizeModule(parentId, chunks[0]) + "!" + window.normalizeModule(parentId, chunks[1]);
67       }
68       // normalize relative requires
69       if (moduleName.charAt(0) == ".") {
70           var base = parentId.split("/").slice(0, -1).join("/");
71           moduleName = (base ? base + "/" : "") + moduleName;
72           
73           while (moduleName.indexOf(".") !== -1 && previous != moduleName) {
74               var previous = moduleName;
75               moduleName = moduleName.replace(/^\.\//, "").replace(/\/\.\//, "/").replace(/[^\/]+\/\.\.\//, "");
76           }
77       }
78       
79       return moduleName;
80   };
81   
82   window.require = function require(parentId, id) {
83       if (!id) {
84           id = parentId;
85           parentId = null;
86       }
87       if (!id.charAt)
88           throw new Error("worker.js require() accepts only (parentId, id) as arguments");
89   
90       id = window.normalizeModule(parentId, id);
91   
92       var module = window.require.modules[id];
93       if (module) {
94           if (!module.initialized) {
95               module.initialized = true;
96               module.exports = module.factory().exports;
97           }
98           return module.exports;
99       }
100     
101      if (!window.require.tlns)
102          return console.log("unable to load " + id);
103      
104      var path = resolveModuleId(id, window.require.tlns);
105      if (path.slice(-3) != ".js") path += ".js";
106      
107      window.require.id = id;
108      window.require.modules[id] = {}; // prevent infinite loop on broken modules
109      importScripts(path);
110      return window.require(parentId, id);
111  };
112  function resolveModuleId(id, paths) {
113      var testPath = id, tail = "";
114      while (testPath) {
115          var alias = paths[testPath];
116          if (typeof alias == "string") {
117              return alias + tail;
118          } else if (alias) {
119              return  alias.location.replace(/\/*$/, "/") + (tail || alias.main || alias.name); 
120          } else if (alias === false) { 
121              return ""; 
122          } 
123          var i = testPath.lastIndexOf("/"); 
124          if (i === -1) break; 
125          tail = testPath.substr(i) + tail; 
126          testPath = testPath.slice(0, i); 
127      } 
128      return id; 
129  } 
130  window.require.modules = {}; 
131  window.require.tlns = {}; 
132   
133  window.define = function(id, deps, factory) { 
134      if (arguments.length == 2) { 
135          factory = deps; 
136          if (typeof id != "string") { 
137              deps = id; 
138              id = window.require.id; 
139          } 
140      } else if (arguments.length == 1) { 
141          factory = id; 
142          deps = []; 
143          id = window.require.id; 
144      } 
145       
146      if (typeof factory != "function") { 
147          window.require.modules[id] = { 
148              exports: factory, 
149              initialized: true 
150          }; 
151          return; 
152      } 
153   
154      if (!deps.length) 
155          // If there is no dependencies, we inject "require", "exports" and 
156          // "module" as dependencies, to provide CommonJS compatibility. 
157          deps = ["require", "exports", "module"]; 
158   
159      var req = function(childId) { 
160          return window.require(id, childId); 
161      }; 
162   
163      window.require.modules[id] = { 
164          exports: {}, 
165          factory: function() { 
166              var module = this; 
167              var returnExports = factory.apply(this, deps.slice(0, factory.length).map(function(dep) { 
168                  switch (dep) { 
169                      // Because "require", "exports" and "module" aren't actual 
170                      // dependencies, we must handle them seperately. 
171                      case "require": return req; 
172                      case "exports": return module.exports; 
173                      case "module":  return module; 
174                      // But for all other dependencies, we can just go ahead and 
175                      // require them. 
176                      default:        return req(dep); 
177                  } 
178              })); 
179              if (returnExports) 
180                  module.exports = returnExports; 
181              return module; 
182          } 
183      }; 
184  }; 
185  window.define.amd = {}; 
186  require.tlns = {}; 
187  window.initBaseUrls  = function initBaseUrls(topLevelNamespaces) { 
188      for (var i in topLevelNamespaces) 
189          require.tlns[i] = topLevelNamespaces[i]; 
190  }; 
191   
192  window.initSender = function initSender() { 
193   
194      var EventEmitter = window.require("ace/lib/event_emitter").EventEmitter; 
195      var oop = window.require("ace/lib/oop"); 
196       
197      var Sender = function() {}; 
198       
199      (function() { 
200           
201          oop.implement(this, EventEmitter); 
202                   
203          this.callback = function(data, callbackId) { 
204              postMessage({ 
205                  type: "call", 
206                  id: callbackId, 
207                  data: data 
208              }); 
209          }; 
210       
211          this.emit = function(name, data) { 
212              postMessage({ 
213                  type: "event", 
214                  name: name, 
215                  data: data 
216              }); 
217          }; 
218           
219      }).call(Sender.prototype); 
220       
221      return new Sender(); 
222  }; 
223   
224  var main = window.main = null; 
225  var sender = window.sender = null; 
226   
227  window.onmessage = function(e) { 
228      var msg = e.data; 
229      if (msg.event && sender) { 
230          sender._signal(msg.event, msg.data); 
231      } 
232      else if (msg.command) { 
233          if (main[msg.command]) 
234              main[msg.command].apply(main, msg.args); 
235          else if (window[msg.command]) 
236              window[msg.command].apply(window, msg.args); 
237          else 
238              throw new Error("Unknown command:" + msg.command); 
239      } 
240      else if (msg.init) { 
241          window.initBaseUrls(msg.tlns); 
242          require("ace/lib/es5-shim"); 
243          sender = window.sender = window.initSender(); 
244          var clazz = require(msg.module)[msg.classname]; 
245          main = window.main = new clazz(sender); 
246      } 
247  }; 
248  })(this);

251  "use strict"; 
252   
253  exports.inherits = function(ctor, superCtor) { 
254      ctor.super_ = superCtor; 
255      ctor.prototype = Object.create(superCtor.prototype, { 
256          constructor: { 
257              value: ctor, 
258              enumerable: false, 
259              writable: true, 
260              configurable: true 
261          } 
262      }); 
263  }; 
264   
265  exports.mixin = function(obj, mixin) { 
266      for (var key in mixin) { 
267          obj[key] = mixin[key]; 
268      } 
269      return obj; 
270  }; 
271   
272  exports.implement = function(proto, mixin) { 
273      exports.mixin(proto, mixin); 
274  };

278  define("ace/range",[], function(require, exports, module) { 
279  "use strict"; 
280  var comparePoints = function(p1, p2) { 
281      return p1.row - p2.row || p1.column - p2.column; 
282  }; 
283  var Range = function(startRow, startColumn, endRow, endColumn) { 
284      this.start = { 
285          row: startRow, 
286          column: startColumn 
287      }; 
288   
289      this.end = { 
290          row: endRow, 
291          column: endColumn 
292      }; 
293  }; 
294   
295  (function() { 
296      this.isEqual = function(range) { 
297          return this.start.row === range.start.row && 
298              this.end.row === range.end.row && 
299              this.start.column === range.start.column && 
300              this.end.column === range.end.column; 
301      }; 
302      this.toString = function() { 
303          return ("Range: [" + this.start.row + "/" + this.start.column + 
304              "] -> [" + this.end.row + "/" + this.end.column + "]"); 
305      }; 
306   
307      this.contains = function(row, column) { 
308          return this.compare(row, column) == 0; 
309      }; 
310      this.compareRange = function(range) { 
311          var cmp, 
312              end = range.end, 
313              start = range.start; 
314   
315          cmp = this.compare(end.row, end.column); 
316          if (cmp == 1) { 
317              cmp = this.compare(start.row, start.column); 
318              if (cmp == 1) { 
319                  return 2; 
320              } else if (cmp == 0) { 
321                  return 1; 
322              } else { 
323                  return 0; 
324              } 
325          } else if (cmp == -1) { 
326              return -2; 
327          } else { 
328              cmp = this.compare(start.row, start.column); 
329              if (cmp == -1) { 
330                  return -1; 
331              } else if (cmp == 1) { 
332                  return 42; 
333              } else { 
334                  return 0; 
335              } 
336          } 
337      }; 
338      this.comparePoint = function(p) { 
339          return this.compare(p.row, p.column); 
340      }; 
341      this.containsRange = function(range) { 
342          return this.comparePoint(range.start) == 0 && this.comparePoint(range.end) == 0; 
343      }; 
344      this.intersects = function(range) { 
345          var cmp = this.compareRange(range); 
346          return (cmp == -1 || cmp == 0 || cmp == 1); 
347      }; 
348      this.isEnd = function(row, column) { 
349          return this.end.row == row && this.end.column == column; 
350      }; 
351      this.isStart = function(row, column) { 
352          return this.start.row == row && this.start.column == column; 
353      }; 
354      this.setStart = function(row, column) { 
355          if (typeof row == "object") { 
356              this.start.column = row.column; 
357              this.start.row = row.row; 
358          } else { 
359              this.start.row = row; 
360              this.start.column = column; 
361          } 
362      }; 
363      this.setEnd = function(row, column) { 
364          if (typeof row == "object") { 
365              this.end.column = row.column; 
366              this.end.row = row.row; 
367          } else { 
368              this.end.row = row; 
369              this.end.column = column; 
370          } 
371      }; 
372      this.inside = function(row, column) { 
373          if (this.compare(row, column) == 0) { 
374              if (this.isEnd(row, column) || this.isStart(row, column)) { 
375                  return false; 
376              } else { 
377                  return true; 
378              } 
379          } 
380          return false; 
381      }; 
382      this.insideStart = function(row, column) { 
383          if (this.compare(row, column) == 0) { 
384              if (this.isEnd(row, column)) { 
385                  return false; 
386              } else { 
387                  return true; 
388              } 
389          } 
390          return false; 
391      }; 
392      this.insideEnd = function(row, column) { 
393          if (this.compare(row, column) == 0) { 
394              if (this.isStart(row, column)) { 
395                  return false; 
396              } else { 
397                  return true; 
398              } 
399          } 
400          return false; 
401      }; 
402      this.compare = function(row, column) { 
403          if (!this.isMultiLine()) { 
404              if (row === this.start.row) { 
405                  return column < this.start.column ? -1 : (column > this.end.column ? 1 : 0); 
406              } 
407          } 
408   
409          if (row < this.start.row) 
410              return -1; 
411   
412          if (row > this.end.row) 
413              return 1; 
414   
415          if (this.start.row === row) 
416              return column >= this.start.column ? 0 : -1; 
417   
418          if (this.end.row === row) 
419              return column <= this.end.column ? 0 : 1; 
420   
421          return 0; 
422      }; 
423      this.compareStart = function(row, column) { 
424          if (this.start.row == row && this.start.column == column) { 
425              return -1; 
426          } else { 
427              return this.compare(row, column); 
428          } 
429      }; 
430      this.compareEnd = function(row, column) { 
431          if (this.end.row == row && this.end.column == column) { 
432              return 1; 
433          } else { 
434              return this.compare(row, column); 
435          } 
436      }; 
437      this.compareInside = function(row, column) { 
438          if (this.end.row == row && this.end.column == column) { 
439              return 1; 
440          } else if (this.start.row == row && this.start.column == column) { 
441              return -1; 
442          } else { 
443              return this.compare(row, column); 
444          } 
445      }; 
446      this.clipRows = function(firstRow, lastRow) { 
447          if (this.end.row > lastRow) 
448              var end = {row: lastRow + 1, column: 0}; 
449          else if (this.end.row < firstRow) 
450              var end = {row: firstRow, column: 0}; 
451   
452          if (this.start.row > lastRow) 
453              var start = {row: lastRow + 1, column: 0}; 
454          else if (this.start.row < firstRow) 
455              var start = {row: firstRow, column: 0}; 
456   
457          return Range.fromPoints(start || this.start, end || this.end); 
458      }; 
459      this.extend = function(row, column) { 
460          var cmp = this.compare(row, column); 
461   
462          if (cmp == 0) 
463              return this; 
464          else if (cmp == -1) 
465              var start = {row: row, column: column}; 
466          else 
467              var end = {row: row, column: column}; 
468   
469          return Range.fromPoints(start || this.start, end || this.end); 
470      }; 
471   
472      this.isEmpty = function() { 
473          return (this.start.row === this.end.row && this.start.column === this.end.column); 
474      }; 
475      this.isMultiLine = function() { 
476          return (this.start.row !== this.end.row); 
477      }; 
478      this.clone = function() { 
479          return Range.fromPoints(this.start, this.end); 
480      }; 
481      this.collapseRows = function() { 
482          if (this.end.column == 0) 
483              return new Range(this.start.row, 0, Math.max(this.start.row, this.end.row-1), 0); 
484          else 
485              return new Range(this.start.row, 0, this.end.row, 0); 
486      }; 
487      this.toScreenRange = function(session) { 
488          var screenPosStart = session.documentToScreenPosition(this.start); 
489          var screenPosEnd = session.documentToScreenPosition(this.end); 
490   
491          return new Range( 
492              screenPosStart.row, screenPosStart.column, 
493              screenPosEnd.row, screenPosEnd.column 
494          ); 
495      }; 
496      this.moveBy = function(row, column) { 
497          this.start.row += row; 
498          this.start.column += column; 
499          this.end.row += row; 
500          this.end.column += column; 
501      }; 
502   
503  }).call(Range.prototype); 
504  Range.fromPoints = function(start, end) { 
505      return new Range(start.row, start.column, end.row, end.column); 
506  }; 
507  Range.comparePoints = comparePoints; 
508   
509  Range.comparePoints = function(p1, p2) { 
510      return p1.row - p2.row || p1.column - p2.column; 
511  }; 
512   
513   
514  exports.Range = Range; 
515  }); 
516   
517  define("ace/apply_delta",[], function(require, exports, module) { 
518  "use strict"; 
519   
520  function throwDeltaError(delta, errorText){ 
521      console.log("Invalid Delta:", delta); 
522      throw "Invalid Delta: " + errorText; 
523  } 
524   
525  function positionInDocument(docLines, position) { 
526      return position.row    >= 0 && position.row    <  docLines.length && 
527             position.column >= 0 && position.column <= docLines[position.row].length; 
528  } 
529   
530  function validateDelta(docLines, delta) { 
531      if (delta.action != "insert" && delta.action != "remove") 
532          throwDeltaError(delta, "delta.action must be 'insert' or 'remove'"); 
533      if (!(delta.lines instanceof Array)) 
534          throwDeltaError(delta, "delta.lines must be an Array"); 
535      if (!delta.start || !delta.end) 
536         throwDeltaError(delta, "delta.start/end must be an present"); 
537      var start = delta.start; 
538      if (!positionInDocument(docLines, delta.start)) 
539          throwDeltaError(delta, "delta.start must be contained in document"); 
540      var end = delta.end; 
541      if (delta.action == "remove" && !positionInDocument(docLines, end)) 
542          throwDeltaError(delta, "delta.end must contained in document for 'remove' actions"); 
543      var numRangeRows = end.row - start.row; 
544      var numRangeLastLineChars = (end.column - (numRangeRows == 0 ? start.column : 0)); 
545      if (numRangeRows != delta.lines.length - 1 || delta.lines[numRangeRows].length != numRangeLastLineChars) 
546          throwDeltaError(delta, "delta.range must match delta lines"); 
547  } 
548   
549  exports.applyDelta = function(docLines, delta, doNotValidate) { 
550      var row = delta.start.row; 
551      var startColumn = delta.start.column; 
552      var line = docLines[row] || ""; 
553      switch (delta.action) { 
554          case "insert": 
555              var lines = delta.lines; 
556              if (lines.length === 1) { 
557                  docLines[row] = line.substring(0, startColumn) + delta.lines[0] + line.substring(startColumn); 
558              } else { 
559                  var args = [row, 1].concat(delta.lines); 
560                  docLines.splice.apply(docLines, args); 
561                  docLines[row] = line.substring(0, startColumn) + docLines[row]; 
562                  docLines[row + delta.lines.length - 1] += line.substring(startColumn); 
563              } 
564              break; 
565          case "remove": 
566              var endColumn = delta.end.column; 
567              var endRow = delta.end.row; 
568              if (row === endRow) { 
569                  docLines[row] = line.substring(0, startColumn) + line.substring(endColumn); 
570              } else { 
571                  docLines.splice( 
572                      row, endRow - row + 1, 
573                      line.substring(0, startColumn) + docLines[endRow].substring(endColumn) 
574                  ); 
575              } 
576              break; 
577      } 
578  }; 
579  });

581  define("ace/lib/event_emitter",[], function(require, exports, module) { 
582  "use strict"; 
583   
584  var EventEmitter = {}; 
585  var stopPropagation = function() { this.propagationStopped = true; }; 
586  var preventDefault = function() { this.defaultPrevented = true; }; 
587   
588  EventEmitter._emit = 
589  EventEmitter._dispatchEvent = function(eventName, e) { 
590      this._eventRegistry || (this._eventRegistry = {}); 
591      this._defaultHandlers || (this._defaultHandlers = {}); 
592   
593      var listeners = this._eventRegistry[eventName] || []; 
594      var defaultHandler = this._defaultHandlers[eventName]; 
595      if (!listeners.length && !defaultHandler) 
596          return; 
597   
598      if (typeof e != "object" || !e) 
599          e = {}; 
600   
601      if (!e.type) 
602          e.type = eventName; 
603      if (!e.stopPropagation) 
604          e.stopPropagation = stopPropagation; 
605      if (!e.preventDefault) 
606          e.preventDefault = preventDefault; 
607   
608      listeners = listeners.slice(); 
609      for (var i=0; i<listeners.length; i++) { 
610          listeners[i](e, this); 
611          if (e.propagationStopped) 
612              break; 
613      } 
614       
615      if (defaultHandler && !e.defaultPrevented) 
616          return defaultHandler(e, this); 
617  }; 
618   
619   
620  EventEmitter._signal = function(eventName, e) { 
621      var listeners = (this._eventRegistry || {})[eventName]; 
622      if (!listeners) 
623          return; 
624      listeners = listeners.slice(); 
625      for (var i=0; i<listeners.length; i++) 
626          listeners[i](e, this); 
627  }; 
628   
629  EventEmitter.once = function(eventName, callback) { 
630      var _self = this; 
631      callback && this.addEventListener(eventName, function newCallback() { 
632          _self.removeEventListener(eventName, newCallback); 
633          callback.apply(null, arguments); 
634      }); 
635  }; 
636   
637   
638  EventEmitter.setDefaultHandler = function(eventName, callback) { 
639      var handlers = this._defaultHandlers; 
640      if (!handlers) 
641          handlers = this._defaultHandlers = {_disabled_: {}}; 
642       
643      if (handlers[eventName]) { 
644          var old = handlers[eventName]; 
645          var disabled = handlers._disabled_[eventName]; 
646          if (!disabled) 
647              handlers._disabled_[eventName] = disabled = []; 
648          disabled.push(old); 
649          var i = disabled.indexOf(callback); 
650          if (i != -1)  
651              disabled.splice(i, 1); 
652      } 
653      handlers[eventName] = callback; 
654  }; 
655  EventEmitter.removeDefaultHandler = function(eventName, callback) { 
656      var handlers = this._defaultHandlers; 
657      if (!handlers) 
658          return; 
659      var disabled = handlers._disabled_[eventName]; 
660       
661      if (handlers[eventName] == callback) { 
662          if (disabled) 
663              this.setDefaultHandler(eventName, disabled.pop()); 
664      } else if (disabled) { 
665          var i = disabled.indexOf(callback); 
666          if (i != -1) 
667              disabled.splice(i, 1); 
668      } 
669  }; 
670   
671  EventEmitter.on = 
672  EventEmitter.addEventListener = function(eventName, callback, capturing) { 
673      this._eventRegistry = this._eventRegistry || {}; 
674   
675      var listeners = this._eventRegistry[eventName]; 
676      if (!listeners) 
677          listeners = this._eventRegistry[eventName] = []; 
678   
679      if (listeners.indexOf(callback) == -1) 
680          listeners[capturing ? "unshift" : "push"](callback); 
681      return callback; 
682  }; 
683   
684  EventEmitter.off = 
685  EventEmitter.removeListener = 
686  EventEmitter.removeEventListener = function(eventName, callback) { 
687      this._eventRegistry = this._eventRegistry || {}; 
688   
689      var listeners = this._eventRegistry[eventName]; 
690      if (!listeners) 
691          return; 
692   
693      var index = listeners.indexOf(callback); 
694      if (index !== -1) 
695          listeners.splice(index, 1); 
696  }; 
697   
698  EventEmitter.removeAllListeners = function(eventName) { 
699      if (this._eventRegistry) this._eventRegistry[eventName] = []; 
700  }; 
701   
702  exports.EventEmitter = EventEmitter; 
703   
704  }); 
705   
706  define("ace/anchor",[], function(require, exports, module) { 
707  "use strict"; 
708   
709  var oop = require("./lib/oop"); 
710  var EventEmitter = require("./lib/event_emitter").EventEmitter; 
711   
712  var Anchor = exports.Anchor = function(doc, row, column) { 
713      this.$onChange = this.onChange.bind(this); 
714      this.attach(doc); 
715       
716      if (typeof column == "undefined") 
717          this.setPosition(row.row, row.column); 
718      else 
719          this.setPosition(row, column); 
720  }; 
721   
722  (function() { 
723   
724      oop.implement(this, EventEmitter); 
725      this.getPosition = function() { 
726          return this.$clipPositionToDocument(this.row, this.column); 
727      }; 
728      this.getDocument = function() { 
729          return this.document; 
730      }; 
731      this.$insertRight = false; 
732      this.onChange = function(delta) { 
733          if (delta.start.row == delta.end.row && delta.start.row != this.row) 
734              return; 
735   
736          if (delta.start.row > this.row) 
737              return; 
738               
739          var point = $getTransformedPoint(delta, {row: this.row, column: this.column}, this.$insertRight); 
740          this.setPosition(point.row, point.column, true); 
741      }; 
742       
743      function $pointsInOrder(point1, point2, equalPointsInOrder) { 
744          var bColIsAfter = equalPointsInOrder ? point1.column <= point2.column : point1.column < point2.column; 
745          return (point1.row < point2.row) || (point1.row == point2.row && bColIsAfter); 
746      } 
747               
748      function $getTransformedPoint(delta, point, moveIfEqual) { 
749          var deltaIsInsert = delta.action == "insert"; 
750          var deltaRowShift = (deltaIsInsert ? 1 : -1) * (delta.end.row    - delta.start.row); 
751          var deltaColShift = (deltaIsInsert ? 1 : -1) * (delta.end.column - delta.start.column); 
752          var deltaStart = delta.start; 
753          var deltaEnd = deltaIsInsert ? deltaStart : delta.end; // Collapse insert range. 
754          if ($pointsInOrder(point, deltaStart, moveIfEqual)) { 
755              return { 
756                  row: point.row, 
757                  column: point.column 
758              }; 
759          } 
760          if ($pointsInOrder(deltaEnd, point, !moveIfEqual)) { 
761              return { 
762                  row: point.row + deltaRowShift, 
763                  column: point.column + (point.row == deltaEnd.row ? deltaColShift : 0) 
764              }; 
765          } 
766          return { 
767              row: deltaStart.row, 
768              column: deltaStart.column 
769          }; 
770      } 
771      this.setPosition = function(row, column, noClip) { 
772          var pos; 
773          if (noClip) { 
774              pos = { 
775                  row: row, 
776                  column: column 
777              }; 
778          } else { 
779              pos = this.$clipPositionToDocument(row, column); 
780          } 
781   
782          if (this.row == pos.row && this.column == pos.column) 
783              return; 
784   
785          var old = { 
786              row: this.row, 
787              column: this.column 
788          }; 
789   
790          this.row = pos.row; 
791          this.column = pos.column; 
792          this._signal("change", { 
793              old: old, 
794              value: pos 
795          }); 
796      }; 
797      this.detach = function() { 
798          this.document.removeEventListener("change", this.$onChange); 
799      }; 
800      this.attach = function(doc) { 
801          this.document = doc || this.document; 
802          this.document.on("change", this.$onChange); 
803      }; 
804      this.$clipPositionToDocument = function(row, column) { 
805          var pos = {}; 
806   
807          if (row >= this.document.getLength()) { 
808              pos.row = Math.max(0, this.document.getLength() - 1); 
809              pos.column = this.document.getLine(pos.row).length; 
810          } 
811          else if (row < 0) { 
812              pos.row = 0; 
813              pos.column = 0; 
814          } 
815          else { 
816              pos.row = row; 
817              pos.column = Math.min(this.document.getLine(pos.row).length, Math.max(0, column)); 
818          } 
819   
820          if (column < 0) 
821              pos.column = 0; 
822   
823          return pos; 
824      }; 
825   
826  }).call(Anchor.prototype); 
827   
828  }); 
829   
830  define("ace/document",[], function(require, exports, module) { 
831  "use strict"; 
832   
833  var oop = require("./lib/oop"); 
834  var applyDelta = require("./apply_delta").applyDelta; 
835  var EventEmitter = require("./lib/event_emitter").EventEmitter; 
836  var Range = require("./range").Range; 
837  var Anchor = require("./anchor").Anchor; 
838   
839  var Document = function(textOrLines) { 
840      this.$lines = [""]; 
841      if (textOrLines.length === 0) { 
842          this.$lines = [""]; 
843      } else if (Array.isArray(textOrLines)) { 
844          this.insertMergedLines({row: 0, column: 0}, textOrLines); 
845      } else { 
846          this.insert({row: 0, column:0}, textOrLines); 
847      } 
848  }; 
849   
850  (function() { 
851   
852      oop.implement(this, EventEmitter); 
853      this.setValue = function(text) { 
854          var len = this.getLength() - 1; 
855          this.remove(new Range(0, 0, len, this.getLine(len).length)); 
856          this.insert({row: 0, column: 0}, text); 
857      }; 
858      this.getValue = function() { 
859          return this.getAllLines().join(this.getNewLineCharacter()); 
860      }; 
861      this.createAnchor = function(row, column) { 
862          return new Anchor(this, row, column); 
863      }; 
864      if ("aaa".split(/a/).length === 0) { 
865          this.$split = function(text) { 
866              return text.replace(/\r\n|\r/g, "\n").split("\n"); 
867          }; 
868      } else { 
869          this.$split = function(text) { 
870              return text.split(/\r\n|\r|\n/); 
871          }; 
872      } 
873   
874   
875      this.$detectNewLine = function(text) { 
876          var match = text.match(/^.*?(\r\n|\r|\n)/m); 
877          this.$autoNewLine = match ? match[1] : "\n"; 
878          this._signal("changeNewLineMode"); 
879      }; 
880      this.getNewLineCharacter = function() { 
881          switch (this.$newLineMode) { 
882            case "windows": 
883              return "\r\n"; 
884            case "unix": 
885              return "\n"; 
886            default: 
887              return this.$autoNewLine || "\n"; 
888          } 
889      }; 
890   
891      this.$autoNewLine = ""; 
892      this.$newLineMode = "auto"; 
893      this.setNewLineMode = function(newLineMode) { 
894          if (this.$newLineMode === newLineMode) 
895              return; 
896   
897          this.$newLineMode = newLineMode; 
898          this._signal("changeNewLineMode"); 
899      }; 
900      this.getNewLineMode = function() { 
901          return this.$newLineMode; 
902      }; 
903      this.isNewLine = function(text) { 
904          return (text == "\r\n" || text == "\r" || text == "\n"); 
905      }; 
906      this.getLine = function(row) { 
907          return this.$lines[row] || ""; 
908      }; 
909      this.getLines = function(firstRow, lastRow) { 
910          return this.$lines.slice(firstRow, lastRow + 1); 
911      }; 
912      this.getAllLines = function() { 
913          return this.getLines(0, this.getLength()); 
914      }; 
915      this.getLength = function() { 
916          return this.$lines.length; 
917      }; 
918      this.getTextRange = function(range) { 
919          return this.getLinesForRange(range).join(this.getNewLineCharacter()); 
920      }; 
921      this.getLinesForRange = function(range) { 
922          var lines; 
923          if (range.start.row === range.end.row) { 
924              lines = [this.getLine(range.start.row).substring(range.start.column, range.end.column)]; 
925          } else { 
926              lines = this.getLines(range.start.row, range.end.row); 
927              lines[0] = (lines[0] || "").substring(range.start.column); 
928              var l = lines.length - 1; 
929              if (range.end.row - range.start.row == l) 
930                  lines[l] = lines[l].substring(0, range.end.column); 
931          } 
932          return lines; 
933      }; 
934      this.insertLines = function(row, lines) { 
935          console.warn("Use of document.insertLines is deprecated. Use the insertFullLines method instead."); 
936          return this.insertFullLines(row, lines); 
937      }; 
938      this.removeLines = function(firstRow, lastRow) { 
939          console.warn("Use of document.removeLines is deprecated. Use the removeFullLines method instead."); 
940          return this.removeFullLines(firstRow, lastRow); 
941      }; 
942      this.insertNewLine = function(position) { 
943          console.warn("Use of document.insertNewLine is deprecated. Use insertMergedLines(position, ['', '']) instead."); 
944          return this.insertMergedLines(position, ["", ""]); 
945      }; 
946      this.insert = function(position, text) { 
947          if (this.getLength() <= 1) 
948              this.$detectNewLine(text); 
949           
950          return this.insertMergedLines(position, this.$split(text)); 
951      }; 
952      this.insertInLine = function(position, text) { 
953          var start = this.clippedPos(position.row, position.column); 
954          var end = this.pos(position.row, position.column + text.length); 
955           
956          this.applyDelta({ 
957              start: start, 
958              end: end, 
959              action: "insert", 
960              lines: [text] 
961          }, true); 
962           
963          return this.clonePos(end); 
964      }; 
965       
966      this.clippedPos = function(row, column) { 
967          var length = this.getLength(); 
968          if (row === undefined) { 
969              row = length; 
970          } else if (row < 0) { 
971              row = 0; 
972          } else if (row >= length) { 
973              row = length - 1; 
974              column = undefined; 
975          } 
976          var line = this.getLine(row); 
977          if (column == undefined) 
978              column = line.length; 
979          column = Math.min(Math.max(column, 0), line.length); 
980          return {row: row, column: column}; 
981      }; 
982       
983      this.clonePos = function(pos) { 
984          return {row: pos.row, column: pos.column}; 
985      }; 
986       
987      this.pos = function(row, column) { 
988          return {row: row, column: column}; 
989      }; 
990       
991      this.$clipPosition = function(position) { 
992          var length = this.getLength(); 
993          if (position.row >= length) { 
994              position.row = Math.max(0, length - 1); 
995              position.column = this.getLine(length - 1).length; 
996          } else { 
997              position.row = Math.max(0, position.row); 
998              position.column = Math.min(Math.max(position.column, 0), this.getLine(position.row).length); 
999          } 
1000         return position; 
1001     }; 
1002     this.insertFullLines = function(row, lines) { 
1003         row = Math.min(Math.max(row, 0), this.getLength()); 
1004         var column = 0; 
1005         if (row < this.getLength()) { 
1006             lines = lines.concat([""]); 
1007             column = 0; 
1008         } else { 
1009             lines = [""].concat(lines); 
1010             row--; 
1011             column = this.$lines[row].length; 
1012         } 
1013         this.insertMergedLines({row: row, column: column}, lines); 
1014     }; 
1015     this.insertMergedLines = function(position, lines) { 
1016         var start = this.clippedPos(position.row, position.column); 
1017         var end = { 
1018             row: start.row + lines.length - 1, 
1019             column: (lines.length == 1 ? start.column : 0) + lines[lines.length - 1].length 
1020         }; 
1021          
1022         this.applyDelta({ 
1023             start: start, 
1024             end: end, 
1025             action: "insert", 
1026             lines: lines 
1027         }); 
1028          
1029         return this.clonePos(end); 
1030     }; 
1031     this.remove = function(range) { 
1032         var start = this.clippedPos(range.start.row, range.start.column); 
1033         var end = this.clippedPos(range.end.row, range.end.column); 
1034         this.applyDelta({ 
1035             start: start, 
1036             end: end, 
1037             action: "remove", 
1038             lines: this.getLinesForRange({start: start, end: end}) 
1039         }); 
1040         return this.clonePos(start); 
1041     }; 
1042     this.removeInLine = function(row, startColumn, endColumn) { 
1043         var start = this.clippedPos(row, startColumn); 
1044         var end = this.clippedPos(row, endColumn); 
1045          
1046         this.applyDelta({ 
1047             start: start, 
1048             end: end, 
1049             action: "remove", 
1050             lines: this.getLinesForRange({start: start, end: end}) 
1051         }, true); 
1052          
1053         return this.clonePos(start); 
1054     }; 
1055     this.removeFullLines = function(firstRow, lastRow) { 
1056         firstRow = Math.min(Math.max(0, firstRow), this.getLength() - 1); 
1057         lastRow  = Math.min(Math.max(0, lastRow ), this.getLength() - 1); 
1058         var deleteFirstNewLine = lastRow == this.getLength() - 1 && firstRow > 0; 
1059         var deleteLastNewLine  = lastRow  < this.getLength() - 1; 
1060         var startRow = ( deleteFirstNewLine ? firstRow - 1                  : firstRow                    ); 
1061         var startCol = ( deleteFirstNewLine ? this.getLine(startRow).length : 0                           ); 
1062         var endRow   = ( deleteLastNewLine  ? lastRow + 1                   : lastRow                     ); 
1063         var endCol   = ( deleteLastNewLine  ? 0                             : this.getLine(endRow).length );  
1064         var range = new Range(startRow, startCol, endRow, endCol); 
1065         var deletedLines = this.$lines.slice(firstRow, lastRow + 1); 
1066          
1067         this.applyDelta({ 
1068             start: range.start, 
1069             end: range.end, 
1070             action: "remove", 
1071             lines: this.getLinesForRange(range) 
1072         }); 
1073         return deletedLines; 
1074     }; 
1075     this.removeNewLine = function(row) { 
1076         if (row < this.getLength() - 1 && row >= 0) { 
1077             this.applyDelta({ 
1078                 start: this.pos(row, this.getLine(row).length), 
1079                 end: this.pos(row + 1, 0), 
1080                 action: "remove", 
1081                 lines: ["", ""] 
1082             }); 
1083         } 
1084     }; 
1085     this.replace = function(range, text) { 
1086         if (!(range instanceof Range)) 
1087             range = Range.fromPoints(range.start, range.end); 
1088         if (text.length === 0 && range.isEmpty()) 
1089             return range.start; 
1090         if (text == this.getTextRange(range)) 
1091             return range.end; 
1092  
1093         this.remove(range); 
1094         var end; 
1095         if (text) { 
1096             end = this.insert(range.start, text); 
1097         } 
1098         else { 
1099             end = range.start; 
1100         } 
1101          
1102         return end; 
1103     }; 
1104     this.applyDeltas = function(deltas) { 
1105         for (var i=0; i<deltas.length; i++) { 
1106             this.applyDelta(deltas[i]); 
1107         } 
1108     }; 
1109     this.revertDeltas = function(deltas) { 
1110         for (var i=deltas.length-1; i>=0; i--) { 
1111             this.revertDelta(deltas[i]); 
1112         } 
1113     }; 
1114     this.applyDelta = function(delta, doNotValidate) { 
1115         var isInsert = delta.action == "insert"; 
1116         if (isInsert ? delta.lines.length <= 1 && !delta.lines[0] 
1117             : !Range.comparePoints(delta.start, delta.end)) { 
1118             return; 
1119         } 
1120          
1121         if (isInsert && delta.lines.length > 20000) { 
1122             this.$splitAndapplyLargeDelta(delta, 20000); 
1123         } 
1124         else { 
1125             applyDelta(this.$lines, delta, doNotValidate); 
1126             this._signal("change", delta); 
1127         } 
1128     }; 
1129      
1130     this.$splitAndapplyLargeDelta = function(delta, MAX) { 
1131         var lines = delta.lines; 
1132         var l = lines.length - MAX + 1; 
1133         var row = delta.start.row;  
1134         var column = delta.start.column; 
1135         for (var from = 0, to = 0; from < l; from = to) { 
1136             to += MAX - 1; 
1137             var chunk = lines.slice(from, to); 
1138             chunk.push(""); 
1139             this.applyDelta({ 
1140                 start: this.pos(row + from, column), 
1141                 end: this.pos(row + to, column = 0), 
1142                 action: delta.action, 
1143                 lines: chunk 
1144             }, true); 
1145         } 
1146         delta.lines = lines.slice(from); 
1147         delta.start.row = row + from; 
1148         delta.start.column = column; 
1149         this.applyDelta(delta, true); 
1150     }; 
1151     this.revertDelta = function(delta) { 
1152         this.applyDelta({ 
1153             start: this.clonePos(delta.start), 
1154             end: this.clonePos(delta.end), 
1155             action: (delta.action == "insert" ? "remove" : "insert"), 
1156             lines: delta.lines.slice() 
1157         }); 
1158     }; 
1159     this.indexToPosition = function(index, startRow) { 
1160         var lines = this.$lines || this.getAllLines(); 
1161         var newlineLength = this.getNewLineCharacter().length; 
1162         for (var i = startRow || 0, l = lines.length; i < l; i++) { 
1163             index -= lines[i].length + newlineLength; 
1164             if (index < 0) 
1165                 return {row: i, column: index + lines[i].length + newlineLength}; 
1166         } 
1167         return {row: l-1, column: index + lines[l-1].length + newlineLength}; 
1168     }; 
1169     this.positionToIndex = function(pos, startRow) { 
1170         var lines = this.$lines || this.getAllLines(); 
1171         var newlineLength = this.getNewLineCharacter().length; 
1172         var index = 0; 
1173         var row = Math.min(pos.row, lines.length); 
1174         for (var i = startRow || 0; i < row; ++i) 
1175             index += lines[i].length + newlineLength; 
1176  
1177         return index + pos.column; 
1178     }; 
1179  
1180 }).call(Document.prototype); 
1181  
1182 exports.Document = Document; 
1183 });

1185 define("ace/lib/lang",[], function(require, exports, module) { 
1186 "use strict"; 
1187  
1188 exports.last = function(a) { 
1189     return a[a.length - 1]; 
1190 }; 
1191  
1192 exports.stringReverse = function(string) { 
1193     return string.split("").reverse().join(""); 
1194 }; 
1195  
1196 exports.stringRepeat = function (string, count) { 
1197     var result = ''; 
1198     while (count > 0) { 
1199         if (count & 1) 
1200             result += string; 
1201  
1202         if (count >>= 1) 
1203             string += string; 
1204     } 
1205     return result; 
1206 };

1208 var trimBeginRegexp = /^\s\s*/;
1209 var trimEndRegexp = /\s\s*$/;
1210 
1211 exports.stringTrimLeft = function (string) {
1212     return string.replace(trimBeginRegexp, '');
1213 };
1214 
1215 exports.stringTrimRight = function (string) {
1216     return string.replace(trimEndRegexp, '');
1217 };

1219 exports.copyObject = function(obj) {
1220     var copy = {};
1221     for (var key in obj) {
1222         copy[key] = obj[key];
1223     }
1224     return copy;
1225 };
1226 
1227 exports.copyArray = function(array){
1228     var copy = [];
1229     for (var i=0, l=array.length; i<l; i++) {
1230         if (array[i] && typeof array[i] == "object")
1231             copy[i] = this.copyObject(array[i]);
1232         else 
1233             copy[i] = array[i];
1234     }
1235     return copy;
1236 };
1237 
1238 exports.deepCopy = function deepCopy(obj) {
1239     if (typeof obj !== "object" || !obj)
1240         return obj;
1241     var copy;
1242     if (Array.isArray(obj)) {
1243         copy = [];
1244         for (var key = 0; key < obj.length; key++) {
1245             copy[key] = deepCopy(obj[key]);
1246         }
1247         return copy;
1248     }
1249     if (Object.prototype.toString.call(obj) !== "[object Object]")
1250         return obj;
1251     
1252     copy = {};
1253     for (var key in obj)
1254         copy[key] = deepCopy(obj[key]);
1255     return copy;
1256 };
1257 
1258 exports.arrayToMap = function(arr) {
1259     var map = {};
1260     for (var i=0; i<arr.length; i++) {
1261         map[arr[i]] = 1;
1262     }
1263     return map;
1264 
1265 };
1266 
1267 exports.createMap = function(props) {
1268     var map = Object.create(null);
1269     for (var i in props) {
1270         map[i] = props[i];
1271     }
1272     return map;
1273 };
1274 exports.arrayRemove = function(array, value) {
1275   for (var i = 0; i <= array.length; i++) {
1276     if (value === array[i]) {
1277       array.splice(i, 1);
1278     }
1279   }
1280 };

1282 exports.escapeRegExp = function(str) {
1283     return str.replace(/([.*+?^${}()|[\]\/\\])/g, '\\$1');
1284 };
1285 
1286 exports.escapeHTML = function(str) {
1287     return ("" + str).replace(/&/g, "&#38;").replace(/"/g, "&#34;").replace(/'/g, "&#39;").replace(/</g, "&#60;");
1288 };
1289 
1290 exports.getMatchOffsets = function(string, regExp) {
1291     var matches = [];
1292 
1293     string.replace(regExp, function(str) {
1294         matches.push({
1295             offset: arguments[arguments.length-2],
1296             length: str.length
1297         });
1298     });
1299 
1300     return matches;
1301 };
1302 exports.deferredCall = function(fcn) {
1303     var timer = null;
1304     var callback = function() {
1305         timer = null;
1306         fcn();
1307     };
1308 
1309     var deferred = function(timeout) {
1310         deferred.cancel();
1311         timer = setTimeout(callback, timeout || 0);
1312         return deferred;
1313     };
1314 
1315     deferred.schedule = deferred;
1316 
1317     deferred.call = function() {
1318         this.cancel();
1319         fcn();
1320         return deferred;
1321     };
1322 
1323     deferred.cancel = function() {
1324         clearTimeout(timer);
1325         timer = null;
1326         return deferred;
1327     };
1328     
1329     deferred.isPending = function() {
1330         return timer;
1331     };
1332 
1333     return deferred;
1334 };
1335 
1336 
1337 exports.delayedCall = function(fcn, defaultTimeout) {
1338     var timer = null;
1339     var callback = function() {
1340         timer = null;
1341         fcn();
1342     };
1343 
1344     var _self = function(timeout) {
1345         if (timer == null)
1346             timer = setTimeout(callback, timeout || defaultTimeout);
1347     };
1348 
1349     _self.delay = function(timeout) {
1350         timer && clearTimeout(timer);
1351         timer = setTimeout(callback, timeout || defaultTimeout);
1352     };
1353     _self.schedule = _self;
1354 
1355     _self.call = function() {
1356         this.cancel();
1357         fcn();
1358     };
1359 
1360     _self.cancel = function() {
1361         timer && clearTimeout(timer);
1362         timer = null;
1363     };
1364 
1365     _self.isPending = function() {
1366         return timer;
1367     };
1368 
1369     return _self;
1370 };
1371 });

1373 define("ace/worker/mirror",[], function(require, exports, module) {
1374 "use strict";
1375 
1376 var Range = require("../range").Range;
1377 var Document = require("../document").Document;
1378 var lang = require("../lib/lang");
1379     
1380 var Mirror = exports.Mirror = function(sender) {
1381     this.sender = sender;
1382     var doc = this.doc = new Document("");
1383     
1384     var deferredUpdate = this.deferredUpdate = lang.delayedCall(this.onUpdate.bind(this));
1385     
1386     var _self = this;
1387     sender.on("change", function(e) {
1388         var data = e.data;
1389         if (data[0].start) {
1390             doc.applyDeltas(data);
1391         } else {
1392             for (var i = 0; i < data.length; i += 2) {
1393                 if (Array.isArray(data[i+1])) {
1394                     var d = {action: "insert", start: data[i], lines: data[i+1]};
1395                 } else {
1396                     var d = {action: "remove", start: data[i], end: data[i+1]};

1474   if (!isNumber(n) || n < 0 || isNaN(n))

1480 EventEmitter.prototype.emit = function(type) {
1481   var er, handler, len, args, i, listeners;
1482 
1483   if (!this._events)
1484     this._events = {};
1485   if (type === 'error') {
1486     if (!this._events.error ||
1487         (isObject(this._events.error) && !this._events.error.length)) {
1488       er = arguments[1];
1489       if (er instanceof Error) {
1490         throw er; // Unhandled 'error' event
1491       }
1492       throw TypeError('Uncaught, unspecified "error" event.');
1493     }
1494   }
1495 
1496   handler = this._events[type];
1497 
1498   if (isUndefined(handler))
1499     return false;
1500 
1501   if (isFunction(handler)) {
1502     switch (arguments.length) {
1503       case 1:
1504         handler.call(this);
1505         break;
1506       case 2:
1507         handler.call(this, arguments[1]);
1508         break;
1509       case 3:
1510         handler.call(this, arguments[1], arguments[2]);
1511         break;
1512       default:
1513         len = arguments.length;
1514         args = new Array(len - 1);
1515         for (i = 1; i < len; i++)
1516           args[i - 1] = arguments[i];
1517         handler.apply(this, args);
1518     }
1519   } else if (isObject(handler)) {
1520     len = arguments.length;
1521     args = new Array(len - 1);
1522     for (i = 1; i < len; i++)
1523       args[i - 1] = arguments[i];
1524 
1525     listeners = handler.slice();
1526     len = listeners.length;
1527     for (i = 0; i < len; i++)
1528       listeners[i].apply(this, args);
1529   }
1530 
1531   return true;
1532 };

1534 EventEmitter.prototype.addListener = function(type, listener) {
1535   var m;
1536 
1537   if (!isFunction(listener))
1538     throw TypeError('listener must be a function');
1539 
1540   if (!this._events)
1541     this._events = {};
1542   if (this._events.newListener)
1543     this.emit('newListener', type,
1544               isFunction(listener.listener) ?
1545               listener.listener : listener);
1546 
1547   if (!this._events[type])
1548     this._events[type] = listener;
1549   else if (isObject(this._events[type]))
1550     this._events[type].push(listener);
1551   else
1552     this._events[type] = [this._events[type], listener];
1553   if (isObject(this._events[type]) && !this._events[type].warned) {
1554     var m;
1555     if (!isUndefined(this._maxListeners)) {
1556       m = this._maxListeners;
1557     } else {
1558       m = EventEmitter.defaultMaxListeners;
1559     }
1560 
1561     if (m && m > 0 && this._events[type].length > m) {
1562       this._events[type].warned = true;
1563       console.error('(node) warning: possible EventEmitter memory ' +
1564                     'leak detected. %d listeners added. ' +
1565                     'Use emitter.setMaxListeners() to increase limit.',
1566                     this._events[type].length);
1567       if (typeof console.trace === 'function') {
1568         console.trace();
1569       }
1570     }
1571   }
1572 
1573   return this;

1598 EventEmitter.prototype.removeListener = function(type, listener) {
1599   var list, position, length, i;
1600 
1601   if (!isFunction(listener))
1602     throw TypeError('listener must be a function');
1603 
1604   if (!this._events || !this._events[type])
1605     return this;
1606 
1607   list = this._events[type];
1608   length = list.length;
1609   position = -1;
1610 
1611   if (list === listener ||
1612       (isFunction(list.listener) && list.listener === listener)) {
1613     delete this._events[type];
1614     if (this._events.removeListener)
1615       this.emit('removeListener', type, listener);
1616 
1617   } else if (isObject(list)) {
1618     for (i = length; i-- > 0;) {
1619       if (list[i] === listener ||
1620           (list[i].listener && list[i].listener === listener)) {
1621         position = i;
1622         break;
1623       }
1624     }
1625 
1626     if (position < 0)
1627       return this;
1628 
1629     if (list.length === 1) {
1630       list.length = 0;
1631       delete this._events[type];
1632     } else {
1633       list.splice(position, 1);
1634     }
1635 
1636     if (this._events.removeListener)
1637       this.emit('removeListener', type, listener);
1638   }
1639 
1640   return this;
1641 };

1643 EventEmitter.prototype.removeAllListeners = function(type) {
1644   var key, listeners;
1645 
1646   if (!this._events)
1647     return this;
1648   if (!this._events.removeListener) {
1649     if (arguments.length === 0)
1650       this._events = {};
1651     else if (this._events[type])
1652       delete this._events[type];
1653     return this;
1654   }
1655   if (arguments.length === 0) {
1656     for (key in this._events) {
1657       if (key === 'removeListener') continue;
1658       this.removeAllListeners(key);
1659     }
1660     this.removeAllListeners('removeListener');
1661     this._events = {};
1662     return this;
1663   }
1664 
1665   listeners = this._events[type];
1666 
1667   if (isFunction(listeners)) {
1668     this.removeListener(type, listeners);
1669   } else {
1670     while (listeners.length)
1671       this.removeListener(type, listeners[listeners.length - 1]);
1672   }
1673   delete this._events[type];
1674 
1675   return this;

2101   function baseClone(value, isDeep, customizer, key, object, stackA, stackB) {
2102     var result;
2103     if (customizer) {
2104       result = object ? customizer(value, key, object) : customizer(value);
2105     }
2106     if (result !== undefined) {
2107       return result;
2108     }
2109     if (!isObject(value)) {
2110       return value;
2111     }
2112     var isArr = isArray(value);
2113     if (isArr) {
2114       result = initCloneArray(value);
2115       if (!isDeep) {
2116         return arrayCopy(value, result);
2117       }
2118     } else {
2119       var tag = objToString.call(value),
2120           isFunc = tag == funcTag;
2121 
2122       if (tag == objectTag || tag == argsTag || (isFunc && !object)) {
2123         result = initCloneObject(isFunc ? {} : value);
2124         if (!isDeep) {
2125           return baseAssign(result, value);
2126         }
2127       } else {
2128         return cloneableTags[tag]
2129           ? initCloneByTag(value, tag, isDeep)
2130           : (object ? value : {});
2131       }
2132     }
2133     stackA || (stackA = []);
2134     stackB || (stackB = []);
2135 
2136     var length = stackA.length;
2137     while (length--) {
2138       if (stackA[length] == value) {
2139         return stackB[length];
2140       }
2141     }
2142     stackA.push(value);
2143     stackB.push(result);
2144 
2145     (isArr ? arrayEach : baseForOwn)(value, function(subValue, key) {
2146       result[key] = baseClone(subValue, isDeep, customizer, key, value, stackA, stackB);
2147     });
2148     return result;
2149   }

2174     if (object == null) {
2175       return;

2178       path = [pathKey];

2189   function baseIsEqual(value, other, customizer, isLoose, stackA, stackB) {
2190     if (value === other) {
2191       return value !== 0 || (1 / value == 1 / other);
2192     }
2193     var valType = typeof value,
2194         othType = typeof other;
2195 
2196     if ((valType != 'function' && valType != 'object' && othType != 'function' && othType != 'object') ||
2197         value == null || other == null) {
2198       return value !== value && other !== other;
2199     }
2200     return baseIsEqualDeep(value, other, baseIsEqual, customizer, isLoose, stackA, stackB);
2201   }

2203   function baseIsEqualDeep(object, other, equalFunc, customizer, isLoose, stackA, stackB) {
2204     var objIsArr = isArray(object),
2205         othIsArr = isArray(other),
2206         objTag = arrayTag,
2207         othTag = arrayTag;
2208 
2209     if (!objIsArr) {
2210       objTag = objToString.call(object);
2211       if (objTag == argsTag) {
2212         objTag = objectTag;
2213       } else if (objTag != objectTag) {
2214         objIsArr = isTypedArray(object);
2215       }
2216     }
2217     if (!othIsArr) {
2218       othTag = objToString.call(other);
2219       if (othTag == argsTag) {
2220         othTag = objectTag;
2221       } else if (othTag != objectTag) {
2222         othIsArr = isTypedArray(other);
2223       }
2224     }
2225     var objIsObj = objTag == objectTag,
2226         othIsObj = othTag == objectTag,
2227         isSameTag = objTag == othTag;
2228 
2229     if (isSameTag && !(objIsArr || objIsObj)) {
2230       return equalByTag(object, other, objTag);
2231     }
2232     if (!isLoose) {
2233       var valWrapped = objIsObj && hasOwnProperty.call(object, '__wrapped__'),
2234           othWrapped = othIsObj && hasOwnProperty.call(other, '__wrapped__');
2235 
2236       if (valWrapped || othWrapped) {
2237         return equalFunc(valWrapped ? object.value() : object, othWrapped ? other.value() : other, customizer, isLoose, stackA, stackB);
2238       }
2239     }
2240     if (!isSameTag) {
2241       return false;
2242     }
2243     stackA || (stackA = []);
2244     stackB || (stackB = []);
2245 
2246     var length = stackA.length;
2247     while (length--) {
2248       if (stackA[length] == object) {
2249         return stackB[length] == other;
2250       }
2251     }
2252     stackA.push(object);
2253     stackB.push(other);
2254 
2255     var result = (objIsArr ? equalArrays : equalObjects)(object, other, equalFunc, customizer, isLoose, stackA, stackB);
2256 
2257     stackA.pop();
2258     stackB.pop();
2259 
2260     return result;
2261   }

2263   function baseIsMatch(object, props, values, strictCompareFlags, customizer) {
2264     var index = -1,
2265         length = props.length,
2266         noCustomizer = !customizer;
2267 
2268     while (++index < length) {
2269       if ((noCustomizer && strictCompareFlags[index])
2270             ? values[index] !== object[props[index]]
2271             : !(props[index] in object)
2272           ) {
2273         return false;
2274       }
2275     }
2276     index = -1;
2277     while (++index < length) {
2278       var key = props[index],
2279           objValue = object[key],
2280           srcValue = values[index];
2281 
2282       if (noCustomizer && strictCompareFlags[index]) {
2283         var result = objValue !== undefined || (key in object);
2284       } else {
2285         result = customizer ? customizer(objValue, srcValue, key) : undefined;
2286         if (result === undefined) {
2287           result = baseIsEqual(srcValue, objValue, customizer, true);
2288         }
2289       }
2290       if (!result) {
2291         return false;
2292       }
2293     }
2294     return true;
2295   }

2297   function baseMatches(source) {
2298     var props = keys(source),
2299         length = props.length;
2300 
2301     if (!length) {
2302       return constant(true);
2303     }
2304     if (length == 1) {
2305       var key = props[0],
2306           value = source[key];
2307 
2308       if (isStrictComparable(value)) {
2309         return function(object) {
2310           if (object == null) {
2311             return false;
2312           }
2313           return object[key] === value && (value !== undefined || (key in toObject(object)));
2314         };
2315       }
2316     }
2317     var values = Array(length),
2318         strictCompareFlags = Array(length);
2319 
2320     while (length--) {
2321       value = source[props[length]];
2322       values[length] = value;
2323       strictCompareFlags[length] = isStrictComparable(value);
2324     }
2325     return function(object) {
2326       return object != null && baseIsMatch(toObject(object), props, values, strictCompareFlags);
2327     };
2328   }

2330   function baseMatchesProperty(path, value) {
2331     var isArr = isArray(path),
2332         isCommon = isKey(path) && isStrictComparable(value),
2333         pathKey = (path + '');
2334 
2335     path = toPath(path);
2336     return function(object) {
2337       if (object == null) {
2338         return false;
2339       }
2340       var key = pathKey;
2341       object = toObject(object);
2342       if ((isArr || !isCommon) && !(key in object)) {
2343         object = path.length == 1 ? object : baseGet(object, baseSlice(path, 0, -1));
2344         if (object == null) {
2345           return false;
2346         }
2347         key = last(path);
2348         object = toObject(object);
2349       }
2350       return object[key] === value
2351         ? (value !== undefined || (key in object))
2352         : baseIsEqual(value, object[key], null, true);
2353     };

2356   function baseMerge(object, source, customizer, stackA, stackB) {
2357     if (!isObject(object)) {
2358       return object;
2359     }
2360     var isSrcArr = isLength(source.length) && (isArray(source) || isTypedArray(source));
2361     if (!isSrcArr) {
2362       var props = keys(source);
2363       push.apply(props, getSymbols(source));
2364     }
2365     arrayEach(props || source, function(srcValue, key) {
2366       if (props) {
2367         key = srcValue;
2368         srcValue = source[key];
2369       }
2370       if (isObjectLike(srcValue)) {
2371         stackA || (stackA = []);
2372         stackB || (stackB = []);
2373         baseMergeDeep(object, source, key, baseMerge, customizer, stackA, stackB);
2374       }
2375       else {
2376         var value = object[key],
2377             result = customizer ? customizer(value, srcValue, key, object, source) : undefined,
2378             isCommon = result === undefined;
2379 
2380         if (isCommon) {
2381           result = srcValue;
2382         }
2383         if ((isSrcArr || result !== undefined) &&
2384             (isCommon || (result === result ? (result !== value) : (value === value)))) {
2385           object[key] = result;
2386         }
2387       }
2388     });
2389     return object;
2390   }

2392   function baseMergeDeep(object, source, key, mergeFunc, customizer, stackA, stackB) {
2393     var length = stackA.length,
2394         srcValue = source[key];
2395 
2396     while (length--) {
2397       if (stackA[length] == srcValue) {
2398         object[key] = stackB[length];
2399         return;
2400       }
2401     }
2402     var value = object[key],
2403         result = customizer ? customizer(value, srcValue, key, object, source) : undefined,
2404         isCommon = result === undefined;
2405 
2406     if (isCommon) {
2407       result = srcValue;
2408       if (isLength(srcValue.length) && (isArray(srcValue) || isTypedArray(srcValue))) {
2409         result = isArray(value)
2410           ? value
2411           : (getLength(value) ? arrayCopy(value) : []);
2412       }
2413       else if (isPlainObject(srcValue) || isArguments(srcValue)) {
2414         result = isArguments(value)
2415           ? toPlainObject(value)
2416           : (isPlainObject(value) ? value : {});
2417       }
2418       else {
2419         isCommon = false;
2420       }
2421     }
2422     stackA.push(srcValue);
2423     stackB.push(result);
2424 
2425     if (isCommon) {
2426       object[key] = mergeFunc(result, srcValue, customizer, stackA, stackB);
2427     } else if (result === result ? (result !== value) : (value === value)) {
2428       object[key] = result;
2429     }
2430   }

2446   function baseSlice(array, start, end) {
2447     var index = -1,
2448         length = array.length;
2449 
2450     start = start == null ? 0 : (+start || 0);
2451     if (start < 0) {
2452       start = -start > length ? 0 : (length + start);
2453     }
2454     end = (end === undefined || end > length) ? length : (+end || 0);
2455     if (end < 0) {
2456       end += length;
2457     }
2458     length = start > end ? 0 : ((end - start) >>> 0);
2459     start >>>= 0;
2460 
2461     var result = Array(length);
2462     while (++index < length) {
2463       result[index] = array[index + start];
2464     }
2465     return result;
2466   }

2489   function binaryIndex(array, value, retHighest) {
2490     var low = 0,
2491         high = array ? array.length : low;
2492 
2493     if (typeof value == 'number' && value === value && high <= HALF_MAX_ARRAY_LENGTH) {
2494       while (low < high) {
2495         var mid = (low + high) >>> 1,
2496             computed = array[mid];
2497 
2498         if (retHighest ? (computed <= value) : (computed < value)) {
2499           low = mid + 1;
2500         } else {
2501           high = mid;
2502         }
2503       }
2504       return high;
2505     }
2506     return binaryIndexBy(array, value, identity, retHighest);
2507   }

2509   function binaryIndexBy(array, value, iteratee, retHighest) {
2510     value = iteratee(value);
2511 
2512     var low = 0,
2513         high = array ? array.length : 0,
2514         valIsNaN = value !== value,
2515         valIsUndef = value === undefined;
2516 
2517     while (low < high) {
2518       var mid = floor((low + high) / 2),
2519           computed = iteratee(array[mid]),
2520           isReflexive = computed === computed;
2521 
2522       if (valIsNaN) {
2523         var setLow = isReflexive || retHighest;
2524       } else if (valIsUndef) {
2525         setLow = isReflexive && (retHighest || computed !== undefined);
2526       } else {
2527         setLow = retHighest ? (computed <= value) : (computed < value);
2528       }
2529       if (setLow) {
2530         low = mid + 1;
2531       } else {
2532         high = mid;
2533       }
2534     }
2535     return nativeMin(high, MAX_ARRAY_INDEX);
2536   }

2538   function bindCallback(func, thisArg, argCount) {
2539     if (typeof func != 'function') {
2540       return identity;
2541     }
2542     if (thisArg === undefined) {
2543       return func;
2544     }
2545     switch (argCount) {
2546       case 1: return function(value) {
2547         return func.call(thisArg, value);
2548       };
2549       case 3: return function(value, index, collection) {
2550         return func.call(thisArg, value, index, collection);
2551       };
2552       case 4: return function(accumulator, value, index, collection) {
2553         return func.call(thisArg, accumulator, value, index, collection);
2554       };
2555       case 5: return function(value, other, key, object, source) {
2556         return func.call(thisArg, value, other, key, object, source);
2557       };
2558     }
2559     return function() {
2560       return func.apply(thisArg, arguments);
2561     };
2562   }

2564   function bufferClone(buffer) {
2565     return bufferSlice.call(buffer, 0);
2566   }
2567   if (!bufferSlice) {
2568     bufferClone = !(ArrayBuffer && Uint8Array) ? constant(null) : function(buffer) {
2569       var byteLength = buffer.byteLength,
2570           floatLength = Float64Array ? floor(byteLength / FLOAT64_BYTES_PER_ELEMENT) : 0,
2571           offset = floatLength * FLOAT64_BYTES_PER_ELEMENT,
2572           result = new ArrayBuffer(byteLength);
2573 
2574       if (floatLength) {
2575         var view = new Float64Array(result, 0, floatLength);
2576         view.set(new Float64Array(buffer, 0, floatLength));
2577       }
2578       if (byteLength != offset) {
2579         view = new Uint8Array(result, offset);
2580         view.set(new Uint8Array(buffer, offset));
2581       }
2582       return result;
2583     };
2584   }

2586   function createAssigner(assigner) {
2587     return restParam(function(object, sources) {
2588       var index = -1,
2589           length = object == null ? 0 : sources.length,
2590           customizer = length > 2 && sources[length - 2],
2591           guard = length > 2 && sources[2],
2592           thisArg = length > 1 && sources[length - 1];
2593 
2594       if (typeof customizer == 'function') {
2595         customizer = bindCallback(customizer, thisArg, 5);
2596         length -= 2;
2597       } else {
2598         customizer = typeof thisArg == 'function' ? thisArg : null;
2599         length -= (customizer ? 1 : 0);
2600       }
2601       if (guard && isIterateeCall(sources[0], sources[1], guard)) {
2602         customizer = length < 3 ? null : customizer;
2603         length = 1;
2604       }
2605       while (++index < length) {
2606         var source = sources[index];
2607         if (source) {
2608           assigner(object, source, customizer);
2609         }
2610       }
2611       return object;
2612     });
2613   }

2615   function createBaseEach(eachFunc, fromRight) {
2616     return function(collection, iteratee) {
2617       var length = collection ? getLength(collection) : 0;
2618       if (!isLength(length)) {
2619         return eachFunc(collection, iteratee);
2620       }
2621       var index = fromRight ? length : -1,
2622           iterable = toObject(collection);
2623 
2624       while ((fromRight ? index-- : ++index < length)) {
2625         if (iteratee(iterable[index], index, iterable) === false) {
2626           break;
2627         }
2628       }
2629       return collection;
2630     };

2668   function equalArrays(array, other, equalFunc, customizer, isLoose, stackA, stackB) {
2669     var index = -1,
2670         arrLength = array.length,
2671         othLength = other.length,
2672         result = true;
2673 
2674     if (arrLength != othLength && !(isLoose && othLength > arrLength)) {
2675       return false;
2676     }
2677     while (result && ++index < arrLength) {
2678       var arrValue = array[index],
2679           othValue = other[index];
2680 
2681       result = undefined;
2682       if (customizer) {
2683         result = isLoose
2684           ? customizer(othValue, arrValue, index)
2685           : customizer(arrValue, othValue, index);
2686       }
2687       if (result === undefined) {
2688         if (isLoose) {
2689           var othIndex = othLength;
2690           while (othIndex--) {
2691             othValue = other[othIndex];
2692             result = (arrValue && arrValue === othValue) || equalFunc(arrValue, othValue, customizer, isLoose, stackA, stackB);
2693             if (result) {
2694               break;
2695             }
2696           }
2697         } else {
2698           result = (arrValue && arrValue === othValue) || equalFunc(arrValue, othValue, customizer, isLoose, stackA, stackB);
2699         }
2700       }
2701     }
2702     return !!result;
2703   }

2705   function equalByTag(object, other, tag) {
2706     switch (tag) {
2707       case boolTag:
2708       case dateTag:
2709         return +object == +other;
2710 
2711       case errorTag:
2712         return object.name == other.name && object.message == other.message;
2713 
2714       case numberTag:
2715         return (object != +object)
2716           ? other != +other
2717           : (object == 0 ? ((1 / object) == (1 / other)) : object == +other);
2718 
2719       case regexpTag:
2720       case stringTag:
2721         return object == (other + '');
2722     }
2723     return false;
2724   }

2726   function equalObjects(object, other, equalFunc, customizer, isLoose, stackA, stackB) {
2727     var objProps = keys(object),
2728         objLength = objProps.length,
2729         othProps = keys(other),
2730         othLength = othProps.length;
2731 
2732     if (objLength != othLength && !isLoose) {
2733       return false;
2734     }
2735     var skipCtor = isLoose,
2736         index = -1;
2737 
2738     while (++index < objLength) {
2739       var key = objProps[index],
2740           result = isLoose ? key in other : hasOwnProperty.call(other, key);
2741 
2742       if (result) {
2743         var objValue = object[key],
2744             othValue = other[key];
2745 
2746         result = undefined;
2747         if (customizer) {
2748           result = isLoose
2749             ? customizer(othValue, objValue, key)
2750             : customizer(objValue, othValue, key);
2751         }
2752         if (result === undefined) {
2753           result = (objValue && objValue === othValue) || equalFunc(objValue, othValue, customizer, isLoose, stackA, stackB);
2754         }
2755       }
2756       if (!result) {
2757         return false;
2758       }
2759       skipCtor || (skipCtor = key == 'constructor');
2760     }
2761     if (!skipCtor) {
2762       var objCtor = object.constructor,
2763           othCtor = other.constructor;
2764 
2765       if (objCtor != othCtor &&
2766           ('constructor' in object && 'constructor' in other) &&
2767           !(typeof objCtor == 'function' && objCtor instanceof objCtor &&
2768             typeof othCtor == 'function' && othCtor instanceof othCtor)) {
2769         return false;
2770       }
2771     }
2772     return true;
2773   }

2775   function getCallback(func, thisArg, argCount) {
2776     var result = lodash.callback || callback;
2777     result = result === callback ? baseCallback : result;
2778     return argCount ? result(func, thisArg, argCount) : result;
2779   }

2783     result = result === indexOf ? baseIndexOf : result;
2784     return collection ? result(collection, target, fromIndex) : result;
2785   }

2793   function initCloneArray(array) {
2794     var length = array.length,

2845   function isIterateeCall(value, index, object) {
2846     if (!isObject(object)) {

2852           prereq = isLength(length) && isIndex(index, length);
2853     } else {
2854       prereq = type == 'string' && index in object;
2855     }
2856     if (prereq) {
2857       var other = object[index];
2858       return value === value ? (value === other) : (other !== other);
2859     }
2860     return false;

2937   function indexOf(array, value, fromIndex) {

2939     if (!length) {
2940       return -1;
2941     }

2944     } else if (fromIndex) {

2946           other = array[index];
2947

2952     }

3026   function restParam(func, start) {
3027     if (typeof func != 'function') {
3028       throw new TypeError(FUNC_ERROR_TEXT);
3029     }
3030     start = nativeMax(start === undefined ? (func.length - 1) : (+start || 0), 0);
3031     return function() {
3032       var args = arguments,
3033           index = -1,
3034           length = nativeMax(args.length - start, 0),
3035           rest = Array(length);
3036 
3037       while (++index < length) {
3038         rest[index] = args[start + index];
3039       }
3040       switch (start) {
3041         case 0: return func.call(this, rest);
3042         case 1: return func.call(this, args[0], rest);
3043         case 2: return func.call(this, args[0], args[1], rest);
3044       }
3045       var otherArgs = Array(start + 1);
3046       index = -1;
3047       while (++index < start) {
3048         otherArgs[index] = args[index];
3049       }
3050       otherArgs[start] = rest;
3051       return func.apply(this, otherArgs);
3052     };
3053   }

3492         state.option.strict = "global";
3493       }
3494     }
3495 
3496     if (state.option.devel) {
3497       combine(predefined, vars.devel);
3498     }
3499 
3500     if (state.option.dojo) {
3501       combine(predefined, vars.dojo);
3502     }
3503 
3504     if (state.option.browser) {
3505       combine(predefined, vars.browser);
3506       combine(predefined, vars.typed);
3507     }
3508 
3509     if (state.option.browserify) {
3510       combine(predefined, vars.browser);
3511       combine(predefined, vars.typed);
3512       combine(predefined, vars.browserify);
3513       if (state.option.strict === true) {
3514         state.option.strict = "global";
3515       }
3516     }
3517 
3518     if (state.option.nonstandard) {
3519       combine(predefined, vars.nonstandard);
3520     }
3521 
3522     if (state.option.jasmine) {
3523       combine(predefined, vars.jasmine);
3524     }
3525 
3526     if (state.option.jquery) {
3527       combine(predefined, vars.jquery);
3528     }
3529 
3530     if (state.option.mootools) {
3531       combine(predefined, vars.mootools);
3532     }
3533 
3534     if (state.option.worker) {
3535       combine(predefined, vars.worker);
3536     }
3537 
3538     if (state.option.wsh) {
3539       combine(predefined, vars.wsh);
3540     }
3541 
3542     if (state.option.globalstrict && state.option.strict !== false) {
3543       state.option.strict = "global";
3544     }
3545 
3546     if (state.option.yui) {
3547       combine(predefined, vars.yui);
3548     }
3549 
3550     if (state.option.mocha) {
3551       combine(predefined, vars.mocha);
3552     }
3553   }
3554   function quit(code, line, chr) {
3555     var percentage = Math.floor((line / state.lines.length) * 100);
3556     var message = messages.errors[code].desc;
3557 
3558     throw {
3559       name: "JSHintError",
3560       line: line,
3561       character: chr,
3562       message: message + " (" + percentage + "% scanned).",
3563       raw: message,
3564       code: code
3565     };
3566   }

3568   function removeIgnoredMessages() {
3569     var ignored = state.ignoredLines;
3570 
3571     if (_.isEmpty(ignored)) return;
3572     JSHINT.errors = _.reject(JSHINT.errors, function(err) { return ignored[err.line] });
3573   }

3575   function warning(code, t, a, b, c, d) {
3576     var ch, l, w, msg;
3577 
3578     if (/^W\d{3}$/.test(code)) {
3579       if (state.ignored[code])
3580         return;
3581 
3582       msg = messages.warnings[code];
3583     } else if (/E\d{3}/.test(code)) {
3584       msg = messages.errors[code];
3585     } else if (/I\d{3}/.test(code)) {
3586       msg = messages.info[code];
3587     }
3588 
3589     t = t || state.tokens.next || {};
3590     if (t.id === "(end)") {  // `~
3591       t = state.tokens.curr;
3592     }
3593 
3594     l = t.line || 0;
3595     ch = t.from || 0;
3596 
3597     w = {
3598       id: "(error)",
3599       raw: msg.desc,
3600       code: msg.code,
3601       evidence: state.lines[l - 1] || "",
3602       line: l,
3603       character: ch,
3604       scope: JSHINT.scope,
3605       a: a,
3606       b: b,
3607       c: c,
3608       d: d
3609     };
3610 
3611     w.reason = supplant(msg.desc, w);
3612     JSHINT.errors.push(w);
3613 
3614     removeIgnoredMessages();
3615 
3616     if (JSHINT.errors.length >= state.option.maxerr)
3617       quit("E043", l, ch);
3618 
3619     return w;
3620   }
