3650   function doOption() {
3651     var nt = state.tokens.next;
3652     var body = nt.body.match(/(-\s+)?[^\s,:]+(?:\s*:\s*(-\s+)?[^\s,]+)?/g) || [];
3653 
3654     var predef = {};
3655     if (nt.type === "globals") {
3656       body.forEach(function(g, idx) {
3657         g = g.split(":");
3658         var key = (g[0] || "").trim();
3659         var val = (g[1] || "").trim();
3660 
3661         if (key === "-" || !key.length) {
3662           if (idx > 0 && idx === body.length - 1) {
3663             return;
3664           }
3665           error("E002", nt);
3666           return;
3667         }
3668 
3669         if (key.charAt(0) === "-") {
3670           key = key.slice(1);
3671           val = false;
3672 
3673           JSHINT.blacklist[key] = key;
3674           delete predefined[key];
3675         } else {
3676           predef[key] = (val === "true");
3677         }
3678       });
3679 
3680       combine(predefined, predef);
3681 
3682       for (var key in predef) {
3683         if (_.has(predef, key)) {
3684           declared[key] = nt;
3685         }
3686       }
3687     }
3688 
3689     if (nt.type === "exported") {
3690       body.forEach(function(e, idx) {
3691         if (!e.length) {
3692           if (idx > 0 && idx === body.length - 1) {
3693             return;
3694           }
3695           error("E002", nt);
3696           return;
3697         }
3698 
3699         state.funct["(scope)"].addExported(e);
3700       });
3701     }
3702 
3703     if (nt.type === "members") {
3704       membersOnly = membersOnly || {};
3705 
3706       body.forEach(function(m) {
3707         var ch1 = m.charAt(0);
3708         var ch2 = m.charAt(m.length - 1);
3709 
3710         if (ch1 === ch2 && (ch1 === "\"" || ch1 === "'")) {
3711           m = m
3712             .substr(1, m.length - 2)
3713             .replace("\\\"", "\"");
3714         }
3715 
3716         membersOnly[m] = false;
3717       });
3718     }
3719 
3720     var numvals = [
3721       "maxstatements",
3722       "maxparams",
3723       "maxdepth",
3724       "maxcomplexity",
3725       "maxerr",
3726       "maxlen",
3727       "indent"
3728     ];
3729 
3730     if (nt.type === "jshint" || nt.type === "jslint") {
3731       body.forEach(function(g) {
3732         g = g.split(":");
3733         var key = (g[0] || "").trim();
3734         var val = (g[1] || "").trim();
3735 
3736         if (!checkOption(key, nt)) {
3737           return;
3738         }
3739 
3740         if (numvals.indexOf(key) >= 0) {
3741           if (val !== "false") {
3742             val = +val;
3743 
3744             if (typeof val !== "number" || !isFinite(val) || val <= 0 || Math.floor(val) !== val) {
3745               error("E032", nt, g[1].trim());
3746               return;
3747             }
3748 
3749             state.option[key] = val;
3750           } else {
3751             state.option[key] = key === "indent" ? 4 : false;
3752           }
3753 
3754           return;
3755         }
3756 
3757         if (key === "validthis") {
3758           if (state.funct["(global)"])
3759             return void error("E009");
3760 
3761           if (val !== "true" && val !== "false")
3762             return void error("E002", nt);
3763 
3764           state.option.validthis = (val === "true");
3765           return;
3766         }
3767 
3768         if (key === "quotmark") {
3769           switch (val) {
3770           case "true":
3771           case "false":
3772             state.option.quotmark = (val === "true");
3773             break;
3774           case "double":
3775           case "single":
3776             state.option.quotmark = val;
3777             break;
3778           default:
3779             error("E002", nt);
3780           }
3781           return;
3782         }
3783 
3784         if (key === "shadow") {
3785           switch (val) {
3786           case "true":
3787             state.option.shadow = true;
3788             break;
3789           case "outer":
3790             state.option.shadow = "outer";
3791             break;
3792           case "false":
3793           case "inner":
3794             state.option.shadow = "inner";
3795             break;
3796           default:
3797             error("E002", nt);
3798           }
3799           return;
3800         }
3801 
3802         if (key === "unused") {
3803           switch (val) {
3804           case "true":
3805             state.option.unused = true;
3806             break;
3807           case "false":
3808             state.option.unused = false;
3809             break;
3810           case "vars":
3811           case "strict":
3812             state.option.unused = val;
3813             break;
3814           default:
3815             error("E002", nt);
3816           }
3817           return;
3818         }
3819 
3820         if (key === "latedef") {
3821           switch (val) {
3822           case "true":
3823             state.option.latedef = true;
3824             break;
3825           case "false":
3826             state.option.latedef = false;
3827             break;
3828           case "nofunc":
3829             state.option.latedef = "nofunc";
3830             break;
3831           default:
3832             error("E002", nt);
3833           }
3834           return;
3835         }
3836 
3837         if (key === "ignore") {
3838           switch (val) {
3839           case "line":
3840             state.ignoredLines[nt.line] = true;
3841             removeIgnoredMessages();
3842             break;
3843           default:
3844             error("E002", nt);
3845           }
3846           return;
3847         }
3848 
3849         if (key === "strict") {
3850           switch (val) {
3851           case "true":
3852             state.option.strict = true;
3853             break;
3854           case "false":
3855             state.option.strict = false;
3856             break;
3857           case "func":
3858           case "global":
3859           case "implied":
3860             state.option.strict = val;
3861             break;
3862           default:
3863             error("E002", nt);
3864           }
3865           return;
3866         }
3867 
3868         if (key === "module") {
3869           if (!hasParsedCode(state.funct)) {
3870             error("E055", state.tokens.next, "module");
3871           }
3872         }
3873         var esversions = {
3874           es3   : 3,
3875           es5   : 5,
3876           esnext: 6
3877         };
3878         if (_.has(esversions, key)) {
3879           switch (val) {
3880           case "true":
3881             state.option.moz = false;
3882             state.option.esversion = esversions[key];
3883             break;
3884           case "false":
3885             if (!state.option.moz) {
3886               state.option.esversion = 5;
3887             }
3888             break;
3889           default:
3890             error("E002", nt);
3891           }
3892           return;
3893         }
3894 
3895         if (key === "esversion") {
3896           switch (val) {
3897           case "5":
3898             if (state.inES5(true)) {
3899               warning("I003");
3900             }
3901           case "3":
3902           case "6":
3903             state.option.moz = false;
3904             state.option.esversion = +val;
3905             break;
3906           case "2015":
3907             state.option.moz = false;
3908             state.option.esversion = 6;
3909             break;
3910           default:
3911             error("E002", nt);
3912           }
3913           if (!hasParsedCode(state.funct)) {
3914             error("E055", state.tokens.next, "esversion");
3915           }
3916           return;
3917         }
3918 
3919         var match = /^([+-])(W\d{3})$/g.exec(key);
3920         if (match) {
3921           state.ignored[match[2]] = (match[1] === "-");
3922           return;
3923         }
3924 
3925         var tn;
3926         if (val === "true" || val === "false") {
3927           if (nt.type === "jslint") {
3928             tn = options.renamed[key] || key;
3929             state.option[tn] = (val === "true");
3930 
3931             if (options.inverted[tn] !== undefined) {
3932               state.option[tn] = !state.option[tn];
3933             }
3934           } else {
3935             state.option[key] = (val === "true");
3936           }
3937 
3938           if (key === "newcap") {
3939             state.option["(explicitNewcap)"] = true;
3940           }
3941           return;
3942         }
3943 
3944         error("E002", nt);
3945       });
3946 
3947       assume();
3948     }
3949   }
3950   function peek(p) {
3951     var i = p || 0, j = lookahead.length, t;
3952 
3953     if (i < j) {
3954       return lookahead[i];
3955     }
3956 
3957     while (j <= i) {
3958       t = lookahead[j];
3959       if (!t) {
3960         t = lookahead[j] = lex.token();
3961       }
3962       j += 1;
3963     }
3964     if (!t && state.tokens.next.id === "(end)") {
3965       return state.tokens.next;
3966     }
3967 
3968     return t;
3969   }
3970 
3971   function peekIgnoreEOL() {
3972     var i = 0;
3973     var t;
3974     do {
3975       t = peek(i++);
3976     } while (t.id === "(endline)");
3977     return t;
3978   }
3979   function advance(id, t) {
3980 
3981     switch (state.tokens.curr.id) {
3982     case "(number)":
3983       if (state.tokens.next.id === ".") {
3984         warning("W005", state.tokens.curr);
3985       }
3986       break;
3987     case "-":
3988       if (state.tokens.next.id === "-" || state.tokens.next.id === "--") {
3989         warning("W006");
3990       }
3991       break;
3992     case "+":
3993       if (state.tokens.next.id === "+" || state.tokens.next.id === "++") {
3994         warning("W007");
3995       }
3996       break;
3997     }
3998 
3999     if (id && state.tokens.next.id !== id) {
4000       if (t) {
4001         if (state.tokens.next.id === "(end)") {
4002           error("E019", t, t.id);
4003         } else {
4004           error("E020", state.tokens.next, id, t.id, t.line, state.tokens.next.value);
4005         }
4006       } else if (state.tokens.next.type !== "(identifier)" || state.tokens.next.value !== id) {
4007         warning("W116", state.tokens.next, id, state.tokens.next.value);
4008       }
4009     }
4010 
4011     state.tokens.prev = state.tokens.curr;
4012     state.tokens.curr = state.tokens.next;
4013     for (;;) {
4014       state.tokens.next = lookahead.shift() || lex.token();
4015 
4016       if (!state.tokens.next) { // No more tokens left, give up
4017         quit("E041", state.tokens.curr.line);
4018       }
4019 
4020       if (state.tokens.next.id === "(end)" || state.tokens.next.id === "(error)") {
4021         return;
4022       }
4023 
4024       if (state.tokens.next.check) {
4025         state.tokens.next.check();
4026       }
4027 
4028       if (state.tokens.next.isSpecial) {
4029         if (state.tokens.next.type === "falls through") {
4030           state.tokens.curr.caseFallsThrough = true;
4031         } else {
4032           doOption();
4033         }
4034       } else {
4035         if (state.tokens.next.id !== "(endline)") {
4036           break;
4037         }
4038       }
4039     }
4040   }

4042   function isInfix(token) {
4043     return token.infix || (!token.identifier && !token.template && !!token.led);
4044   }

4046   function isEndOfExpr() {
4047     var curr = state.tokens.curr;
4048     var next = state.tokens.next;
4049     if (next.id === ";" || next.id === "}" || next.id === ":") {
4050       return true;
4051     }
4052     if (isInfix(next) === isInfix(curr) || (curr.id === "yield" && state.inMoz())) {
4053       return curr.line !== startLine(next);
4054     }
4055     return false;
4056   }
4057 
4058   function isBeginOfExpr(prev) {
4059     return !prev.left && prev.arity !== "unary";
4060   }
4061   function expression(rbp, initial) {
4062     var left, isArray = false, isObject = false, isLetExpr = false;
4063 
4064     state.nameStack.push();
4065     if (!initial && state.tokens.next.value === "let" && peek(0).value === "(") {
4066       if (!state.inMoz()) {
4067         warning("W118", state.tokens.next, "let expressions");
4068       }
4069       isLetExpr = true;
4070       state.funct["(scope)"].stack();
4071       advance("let");
4072       advance("(");
4073       state.tokens.prev.fud();
4074       advance(")");
4075     }
4076 
4077     if (state.tokens.next.id === "(end)")
4078       error("E006", state.tokens.curr);
4079 
4080     var isDangerous =
4081       state.option.asi &&
4082       state.tokens.prev.line !== startLine(state.tokens.curr) &&
4083       _.contains(["]", ")"], state.tokens.prev.id) &&
4084       _.contains(["[", "("], state.tokens.curr.id);
4085 
4086     if (isDangerous)
4087       warning("W014", state.tokens.curr, state.tokens.curr.id);
4088 
4089     advance();
4090 
4091     if (initial) {
4092       state.funct["(verb)"] = state.tokens.curr.value;
4093       state.tokens.curr.beginsStmt = true;
4094     }
4095 
4096     if (initial === true && state.tokens.curr.fud) {
4097       left = state.tokens.curr.fud();
4098     } else {
4099       if (state.tokens.curr.nud) {
4100         left = state.tokens.curr.nud();
4101       } else {
4102         error("E030", state.tokens.curr, state.tokens.curr.id);
4103       }
4104       while ((rbp < state.tokens.next.lbp || state.tokens.next.type === "(template)") &&
4105               !isEndOfExpr()) {
4106         isArray = state.tokens.curr.value === "Array";
4107         isObject = state.tokens.curr.value === "Object";
4108         if (left && (left.value || (left.first && left.first.value))) {
4109           if (left.value !== "new" ||
4110             (left.first && left.first.value && left.first.value === ".")) {
4111             isArray = false;
4112             if (left.value !== state.tokens.curr.value) {
4113               isObject = false;
4114             }
4115           }
4116         }
4117 
4118         advance();
4119 
4120         if (isArray && state.tokens.curr.id === "(" && state.tokens.next.id === ")") {
4121           warning("W009", state.tokens.curr);
4122         }
4123 
4124         if (isObject && state.tokens.curr.id === "(" && state.tokens.next.id === ")") {
4125           warning("W010", state.tokens.curr);
4126         }
4127 
4128         if (left && state.tokens.curr.led) {
4129           left = state.tokens.curr.led(left);
4130         } else {
4131           error("E033", state.tokens.curr, state.tokens.curr.id);
4132         }
4133       }
4134     }
4135     if (isLetExpr) {
4136       state.funct["(scope)"].unstack();
4137     }
4138 
4139     state.nameStack.pop();
4140 
4141     return left;
4142   }
4143   function startLine(token) {
4144     return token.startLine || token.line;
4145   }

4147   function nobreaknonadjacent(left, right) {

4150     if (!state.option.laxbreak && left.line !== startLine(right)) {
4151       warning("W014", right, right.value);
4152     }

4158       warning("E022", t, t.value);

4162   function nobreakcomma(left, right) {
4163     if (left.line !== startLine(right)) {
4164       if (!state.option.laxcomma) {
4165         if (comma.first) {
4166           warning("I001");
4167           comma.first = false;
4168         }
4169         warning("W014", left, right.value);
4170       }
4171     }
4172   }

4174   function comma(opts) {
4175     opts = opts || {};
4176 
4177     if (!opts.peek) {
4178       nobreakcomma(state.tokens.curr, state.tokens.next);
4179       advance(",");
4180     } else {
4181       nobreakcomma(state.tokens.prev, state.tokens.curr);
4182     }
4183 
4184     if (state.tokens.next.identifier && !(opts.property && state.inES5())) {
4185       switch (state.tokens.next.value) {
4186       case "break":
4187       case "case":
4188       case "catch":
4189       case "continue":
4190       case "default":
4191       case "do":
4192       case "else":
4193       case "finally":
4194       case "for":
4195       case "if":
4196       case "in":
4197       case "instanceof":
4198       case "return":
4199       case "switch":
4200       case "throw":
4201       case "try":
4202       case "var":
4203       case "let":
4204       case "while":
4205       case "with":
4206         error("E024", state.tokens.next, state.tokens.next.value);
4207         return false;
4208       }
4209     }
4210 
4211     if (state.tokens.next.type === "(punctuator)") {
4212       switch (state.tokens.next.value) {
4213       case "}":
4214       case "]":
4215       case ",":
4216         if (opts.allowTrailing) {
4217           return true;
4218         }
4219       case ")":
4220         error("E024", state.tokens.next, state.tokens.next.value);
4221         return false;
4222       }
4223     }
4224     return true;
4225   }
4226   function symbol(s, p) {
4227     var x = state.syntax[s];
4228     if (!x || typeof x !== "object") {
4229       state.syntax[s] = x = {
4230         id: s,
4231         lbp: p,
4232         value: s
4233       };
4234     }
4235     return x;
4236   }

4239     var x = symbol(s, 0);
4240     x.delim = true;
4241     return x;

4257   function reserveName(x) {
4258     var c = x.id.charAt(0);
4259     if ((c >= "a" && c <= "z") || (c >= "A" && c <= "Z")) {
4260       x.identifier = x.reserved = true;
4261     }
4262     return x;
4263   }

4265   function prefix(s, f) {
4266     var x = symbol(s, 150);
4267     reserveName(x);
4268 
4269     x.nud = (typeof f === "function") ? f : function() {
4270       this.arity = "unary";
4271       this.right = expression(150);
4272 
4273       if (this.id === "++" || this.id === "--") {
4274         if (state.option.plusplus) {
4275           warning("W016", this, this.id);
4276         } else if (this.right && (!this.right.identifier || isReserved(this.right)) &&
4277             this.right.id !== "." && this.right.id !== "[") {
4278           warning("W017", this);
4279         }
4280 
4281         if (this.right && this.right.isMetaProperty) {
4282           error("E031", this);
4283         } else if (this.right && this.right.identifier) {
4284           state.funct["(scope)"].block.modify(this.right.value, this);
4285         }
4286       }
4287 
4288       return this;
4289     };
4290 
4291     return x;
4292   }

4333   function infix(s, f, p, w) {
4334     var x = symbol(s, p);
4335     reserveName(x);
4336     x.infix = true;
4337     x.led = function(left) {
4338       if (!w) {
4339         nobreaknonadjacent(state.tokens.prev, state.tokens.curr);
4340       }
4341       if ((s === "in" || s === "instanceof") && left.id === "!") {
4342         warning("W018", left, "!");
4343       }
4344       if (typeof f === "function") {
4345         return f(left, this);
4346       } else {
4347         this.left = left;
4348         this.right = expression(p);
4349         return this;
4350       }
4351     };
4352     return x;
4353   }

4368   function relation(s, f) {
4369     var x = symbol(s, 100);
4370 
4371     x.led = function(left) {
4372       nobreaknonadjacent(state.tokens.prev, state.tokens.curr);
4373       this.left = left;
4374       var right = this.right = expression(100);
4375 
4376       if (isIdentifier(left, "NaN") || isIdentifier(right, "NaN")) {
4377         warning("W019", this);
4378       } else if (f) {
4379         f.apply(this, [left, right]);
4380       }
4381 
4382       if (!left || !right) {
4383         quit("E041", state.tokens.curr.line);
4384       }
4385 
4386       if (left.id === "!") {
4387         warning("W018", left, "!");
4388       }
4389 
4390       if (right.id === "!") {
4391         warning("W018", right, "!");
4392       }
4393 
4394       return this;
4395     };
4396     return x;
4397   }

4399   function isPoorRelation(node) {
4400     return node &&
4401         ((node.type === "(number)" && +node.value === 0) ||
4402          (node.type === "(string)" && node.value === "") ||
4403          (node.type === "null" && !state.option.eqnull) ||
4404         node.type === "true" ||
4405         node.type === "false" ||
4406         node.type === "undefined");

4409   var typeofValues = {};
4410   typeofValues.legacy = [
4411     "xml",
4412     "unknown"
4413   ];
4414   typeofValues.es3 = [
4415     "undefined", "boolean", "number", "string", "function", "object",
4416   ];
4417   typeofValues.es3 = typeofValues.es3.concat(typeofValues.legacy);
4418   typeofValues.es6 = typeofValues.es3.concat("symbol");
4419   function isTypoTypeof(left, right, state) {
4420     var values;
4421 
4422     if (state.option.notypeof)
4423       return false;
4424 
4425     if (!left || !right)
4426       return false;
4427 
4428     values = state.inES6() ? typeofValues.es6 : typeofValues.es3;
4429 
4430     if (right.type === "(identifier)" && right.value === "typeof" && left.type === "(string)")
4431       return !_.contains(values, left.value);
4432 
4433     return false;
4434   }

4436   function isGlobalEval(left, state) {
4437     var isGlobal = false;
4438     if (left.type === "this" && state.funct["(context)"] === null) {
4439       isGlobal = true;
4440     }
4441     else if (left.type === "(identifier)") {
4442       if (state.option.node && left.value === "global") {
4443         isGlobal = true;
4444       }
4445 
4446       else if (state.option.browser && (left.value === "window" || left.value === "document")) {
4447         isGlobal = true;
4448       }
4449     }
4450 
4451     return isGlobal;
4452   }

4454   function findNativePrototype(left) {
4455     var natives = [
4456       "Array", "ArrayBuffer", "Boolean", "Collator", "DataView", "Date",
4457       "DateTimeFormat", "Error", "EvalError", "Float32Array", "Float64Array",
4458       "Function", "Infinity", "Intl", "Int16Array", "Int32Array", "Int8Array",
4459       "Iterator", "Number", "NumberFormat", "Object", "RangeError",
4460       "ReferenceError", "RegExp", "StopIteration", "String", "SyntaxError",
4461       "TypeError", "Uint16Array", "Uint32Array", "Uint8Array", "Uint8ClampedArray",
4462       "URIError"
4463     ];
4464 
4465     function walkPrototype(obj) {
4466       if (typeof obj !== "object") return;
4467       return obj.right === "prototype" ? obj : walkPrototype(obj.left);
4468     }
4469 
4470     function walkNative(obj) {
4471       while (!obj.identifier && typeof obj.left === "object")
4472         obj = obj.left;
4473 
4474       if (obj.identifier && natives.indexOf(obj.value) >= 0)
4475         return obj.value;
4476     }
4477 
4478     var prototype = walkPrototype(left);
4479     if (prototype) return walkNative(prototype);
4480   }
4481   function checkLeftSideAssign(left, assignToken, options) {
4482 
4483     var allowDestructuring = options && options.allowDestructuring;
4484 
4485     assignToken = assignToken || left;
4486 
4487     if (state.option.freeze) {
4488       var nativeObject = findNativePrototype(left);
4489       if (nativeObject)
4490         warning("W121", left, nativeObject);
4491     }
4492 
4493     if (left.identifier && !left.isMetaProperty) {
4494       state.funct["(scope)"].block.reassign(left.value, left);
4495     }
4496 
4497     if (left.id === ".") {
4498       if (!left.left || left.left.value === "arguments" && !state.isStrict()) {
4499         warning("E031", assignToken);
4500       }
4501 
4502       state.nameStack.set(state.tokens.prev);
4503       return true;
4504     } else if (left.id === "{" || left.id === "[") {
4505       if (allowDestructuring && state.tokens.curr.left.destructAssign) {
4506         state.tokens.curr.left.destructAssign.forEach(function(t) {
4507           if (t.id) {
4508             state.funct["(scope)"].block.modify(t.id, t.token);
4509           }
4510         });
4511       } else {
4512         if (left.id === "{" || !left.left) {
4513           warning("E031", assignToken);
4514         } else if (left.left.value === "arguments" && !state.isStrict()) {
4515           warning("E031", assignToken);
4516         }
4517       }
4518 
4519       if (left.id === "[") {
4520         state.nameStack.set(left.right);
4521       }
4522 
4523       return true;
4524     } else if (left.isMetaProperty) {
4525       error("E031", assignToken);
4526       return true;
4527     } else if (left.identifier && !isReserved(left)) {
4528       if (state.funct["(scope)"].labeltype(left.value) === "exception") {
4529         warning("W022", left);
4530       }
4531       state.nameStack.set(left);
4532       return true;
4533     }
4534 
4535     if (left === state.syntax["function"]) {
4536       warning("W023", state.tokens.curr);
4537     }
4538 
4539     return false;
4540   }

4542   function assignop(s, f, p) {
4543     var x = infix(s, typeof f === "function" ? f : function(left, that) {
4544       that.left = left;
4545

4547         that.right = expression(10);
4548         return that;
4549       }
4550 
4551       error("E031", that);
4552     }, p);
4553 
4554     x.exps = true;
4555     x.assign = true;
4556     return x;
4557   }

4589     var x = symbol(s, 150);
4590 
4591     x.led = function(left) {
4592       if (state.option.plusplus) {
4593         warning("W016", this, this.id);
4594       } else if ((!left.identifier || isReserved(left)) && left.id !== "." && left.id !== "[") {
4595         warning("W017", this);
4596       }
4597 
4598       if (left.isMetaProperty) {
4599         error("E031", this);
4600       } else if (left && left.identifier) {
4601         state.funct["(scope)"].block.modify(left.value, left);
4602       }
4603

4605       return this;

4609   function optionalidentifier(fnparam, prop, preserve) {
4610     if (!state.tokens.next.identifier) {
4611       return;
4612     }
4613 
4614     if (!preserve) {
4615       advance();
4616     }
4617 
4618     var curr = state.tokens.curr;
4619     var val  = state.tokens.curr.value;
4620 
4621     if (!isReserved(curr)) {
4622       return val;
4623     }
4624 
4625     if (prop) {
4626       if (state.inES5()) {
4627         return val;
4628       }
4629     }
4630 
4631     if (fnparam && val === "undefined") {
4632       return val;
4633     }
4634 
4635     warning("W024", state.tokens.curr, state.tokens.curr.id);
4636     return val;
4637   }
4638   function identifier(fnparam, prop) {
4639     var i = optionalidentifier(fnparam, prop, false);
4640     if (i) {
4641       return i;
4642     }
4643     if (state.tokens.next.value === "...") {
4644       if (!state.inES6(true)) {
4645         warning("W119", state.tokens.next, "spread/rest operator", "6");
4646       }
4647       advance();
4648 
4649       if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "...")) {
4650         warning("E024", state.tokens.next, "...");
4651         while (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "...")) {
4652           advance();
4653         }
4654       }
4655 
4656       if (!state.tokens.next.identifier) {
4657         warning("E024", state.tokens.curr, "...");
4658         return;
4659       }
4660 
4661       return identifier(fnparam, prop);
4662     } else {
4663       error("E030", state.tokens.next, state.tokens.next.value);
4664       if (state.tokens.next.id !== ";") {
4665         advance();
4666       }
4667     }
4668   }

4671   function reachable(controlToken) {
4672     var i = 0, t;
4673     if (state.tokens.next.id !== ";" || controlToken.inBracelessBlock) {
4674       return;
4675     }
4676     for (;;) {
4677       do {
4678         t = peek(i);
4679         i += 1;
4680       } while (t.id !== "(end)" && t.id === "(comment)");
4681 
4682       if (t.reach) {
4683         return;
4684       }
4685       if (t.id !== "(endline)") {
4686         if (t.id === "function") {
4687           if (state.option.latedef === true) {
4688             warning("W026", t);
4689           }
4690           break;
4691         }
4692 
4693         warning("W027", t, t.value, controlToken.value);
4694         break;
4695       }
4696     }
4697   }

4699   function parseFinalSemicolon() {
4700     if (state.tokens.next.id !== ";") {
4701       if (state.tokens.next.isUnclosed) return advance();
4702 
4703       var sameLine = startLine(state.tokens.next) === state.tokens.curr.line &&
4704                      state.tokens.next.id !== "(end)";
4705       var blockEnd = checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "}");
4706 
4707       if (sameLine && !blockEnd) {
4708         errorAt("E058", state.tokens.curr.line, state.tokens.curr.character);
4709       } else if (!state.option.asi) {
4710         if ((blockEnd && !state.option.lastsemic) || !sameLine) {
4711           warningAt("W033", state.tokens.curr.line, state.tokens.curr.character);
4712         }
4713       }
4714     } else {
4715       advance(";");
4716     }
4717   }

4719   function statement() {
4720     var i = indent, r, t = state.tokens.next, hasOwnScope = false;
4721 
4722     if (t.id === ";") {
4723       advance(";");
4724       return;
4725     }
4726     var res = isReserved(t);
4727     if (res && t.meta && t.meta.isFutureReservedWord && peek().id === ":") {
4728       warning("W024", t, t.id);
4729       res = false;
4730     }
4731 
4732     if (t.identifier && !res && peek().id === ":") {
4733       advance();
4734       advance(":");
4735 
4736       hasOwnScope = true;
4737       state.funct["(scope)"].stack();
4738       state.funct["(scope)"].block.addBreakLabel(t.value, { token: state.tokens.curr });
4739 
4740       if (!state.tokens.next.labelled && state.tokens.next.value !== "{") {
4741         warning("W028", state.tokens.next, t.value, state.tokens.next.value);
4742       }
4743 
4744       state.tokens.next.label = t.value;
4745       t = state.tokens.next;
4746     }
4747     if (t.id === "{") {
4748       //
4749       var iscase = (state.funct["(verb)"] === "case" && state.tokens.curr.value === ":");
4750       block(true, true, false, false, iscase);
4751       return;
4752     }
4753     r = expression(0, true);
4754 
4755     if (r && !(r.identifier && r.value === "function") &&
4756         !(r.type === "(punctuator)" && r.left &&
4757           r.left.identifier && r.left.value === "function")) {
4758       if (!state.isStrict() &&
4759           state.option.strict === "global") {
4760         warning("E007");
4761       }
4762     }
4763     if (!t.block) {
4764       if (!state.option.expr && (!r || !r.exps)) {
4765         warning("W030", state.tokens.curr);
4766       } else if (state.option.nonew && r && r.left && r.id === "(" && r.left.id === "new") {
4767         warning("W031", t);
4768       }
4769       parseFinalSemicolon();
4770     }
4771     indent = i;
4772     if (hasOwnScope) {
4773       state.funct["(scope)"].unstack();
4774     }
4775     return r;
4776   }

4779   function statements() {
4780     var a = [], p;
4781 
4782     while (!state.tokens.next.reach && state.tokens.next.id !== "(end)") {
4783       if (state.tokens.next.id === ";") {
4784         p = peek();
4785 
4786         if (!p || (p.id !== "(" && p.id !== "[")) {
4787           warning("W032");
4788         }
4789 
4790         advance(";");
4791       } else {
4792         a.push(statement());
4793       }
4794     }
4795     return a;
4796   }
4797   function directives() {
4798     var i, p, pn;
4799 
4800     while (state.tokens.next.id === "(string)") {
4801       p = peek(0);
4802       if (p.id === "(endline)") {
4803         i = 1;
4804         do {
4805           pn = peek(i++);
4806         } while (pn.id === "(endline)");
4807         if (pn.id === ";") {
4808           p = pn;
4809         } else if (pn.value === "[" || pn.value === ".") {
4810           break;
4811         } else if (!state.option.asi || pn.value === "(") {
4812           warning("W033", state.tokens.next);
4813         }
4814       } else if (p.id === "." || p.id === "[") {
4815         break;
4816       } else if (p.id !== ";") {
4817         warning("W033", p);
4818       }
4819 
4820       advance();
4821       var directive = state.tokens.curr.value;
4822       if (state.directive[directive] ||
4823           (directive === "use strict" && state.option.strict === "implied")) {
4824         warning("W034", state.tokens.curr, directive);
4825       }
4826       state.directive[directive] = true;
4827 
4828       if (p.id === ";") {
4829         advance(";");
4830       }
4831     }
4832 
4833     if (state.isStrict()) {
4834       if (!state.option["(explicitNewcap)"]) {
4835         state.option.newcap = true;
4836       }
4837       state.option.undef = true;
4838     }
4839   }
4840   function block(ordinary, stmt, isfunc, isfatarrow, iscase) {
4841     var a,
4842       b = inblock,
4843       old_indent = indent,
4844       m,
4845       t,
4846       line,
4847       d;
4848 
4849     inblock = ordinary;
4850 
4851     t = state.tokens.next;
4852 
4853     var metrics = state.funct["(metrics)"];
4854     metrics.nestedBlockDepth += 1;
4855     metrics.verifyMaxNestedBlockDepthPerFunction();
4856 
4857     if (state.tokens.next.id === "{") {
4858       advance("{");
4859       state.funct["(scope)"].stack();
4860 
4861       line = state.tokens.curr.line;
4862       if (state.tokens.next.id !== "}") {
4863         indent += state.option.indent;
4864         while (!ordinary && state.tokens.next.from > indent) {
4865           indent += state.option.indent;
4866         }
4867 
4868         if (isfunc) {
4869           m = {};
4870           for (d in state.directive) {
4871             if (_.has(state.directive, d)) {
4872               m[d] = state.directive[d];
4873             }
4874           }
4875           directives();
4876 
4877           if (state.option.strict && state.funct["(context)"]["(global)"]) {
4878             if (!m["use strict"] && !state.isStrict()) {
4879               warning("E007");
4880             }
4881           }
4882         }
4883 
4884         a = statements();
4885 
4886         metrics.statementCount += a.length;
4887 
4888         indent -= state.option.indent;
4889       }
4890 
4891       advance("}", t);
4892 
4893       if (isfunc) {
4894         state.funct["(scope)"].validateParams();
4895         if (m) {
4896           state.directive = m;
4897         }
4898       }
4899 
4900       state.funct["(scope)"].unstack();
4901 
4902       indent = old_indent;
4903     } else if (!ordinary) {
4904       if (isfunc) {
4905         state.funct["(scope)"].stack();
4906 
4907         m = {};
4908         if (stmt && !isfatarrow && !state.inMoz()) {
4909           error("W118", state.tokens.curr, "function closure expressions");
4910         }
4911 
4912         if (!stmt) {
4913           for (d in state.directive) {
4914             if (_.has(state.directive, d)) {
4915               m[d] = state.directive[d];
4916             }
4917           }
4918         }
4919         expression(10);
4920 
4921         if (state.option.strict && state.funct["(context)"]["(global)"]) {
4922           if (!m["use strict"] && !state.isStrict()) {
4923             warning("E007");
4924           }
4925         }
4926 
4927         state.funct["(scope)"].unstack();
4928       } else {
4929         error("E021", state.tokens.next, "{", state.tokens.next.value);
4930       }
4931     } else {
4932       state.funct["(noblockscopedvar)"] = state.tokens.next.id !== "for";
4933       state.funct["(scope)"].stack();
4934 
4935       if (!stmt || state.option.curly) {
4936         warning("W116", state.tokens.next, "{", state.tokens.next.value);
4937       }
4938 
4939       state.tokens.next.inBracelessBlock = true;
4940       indent += state.option.indent;
4941       a = [statement()];
4942       indent -= state.option.indent;
4943 
4944       state.funct["(scope)"].unstack();
4945       delete state.funct["(noblockscopedvar)"];
4946     }
4947     switch (state.funct["(verb)"]) {
4948     case "break":
4949     case "continue":
4950     case "return":
4951     case "throw":
4952       if (iscase) {
4953         break;
4954       }
4955     default:
4956       state.funct["(verb)"] = null;
4957     }

5652     }
5653 
5654     advance("for");
5655     if (state.tokens.next.value === "each") {
5656       advance("each");
5657       if (!state.inMoz()) {
5658         warning("W118", state.tokens.curr, "for each");
5659       }
5660     }
5661     advance("(");
5662     state.funct["(comparray)"].setState("define");
5663     res.left = expression(130);
5664     if (_.contains(["in", "of"], state.tokens.next.value)) {
5665       advance();
5666     } else {
5667       error("E045", state.tokens.curr);
5668     }
5669     state.funct["(comparray)"].setState("generate");
5670     expression(10);
5671 
5672     advance(")");
5673     if (state.tokens.next.value === "if") {
5674       advance("if");
5675       advance("(");
5676       state.funct["(comparray)"].setState("filter");
5677       res.filter = expression(10);
5678       advance(")");
5679     }
5680 
5681     if (!reversed) {
5682       state.funct["(comparray)"].setState("use");
5683       res.right = expression(10);
5684     }
5685 
5686     advance("]");
5687     state.funct["(comparray)"].unstack();
5688     return res;
5689   }
5690 
5691   prefix("[", function() {
5692     var blocktype = lookupBlockType();
5693     if (blocktype.isCompArray) {
5694       if (!state.option.esnext && !state.inMoz()) {
5695         warning("W118", state.tokens.curr, "array comprehension");
5696       }
5697       return comprehensiveArrayExpression();
5698     } else if (blocktype.isDestAssign) {
5699       this.destructAssign = destructuringPattern({ openingParsed: true, assignment: true });
5700       return this;
5701     }
5702     var b = state.tokens.curr.line !== startLine(state.tokens.next);
5703     this.first = [];
5704     if (b) {
5705       indent += state.option.indent;
5706       if (state.tokens.next.from === indent + state.option.indent) {
5707         indent += state.option.indent;
5708       }
5709     }
5710     while (state.tokens.next.id !== "(end)") {
5711       while (state.tokens.next.id === ",") {
5712         if (!state.option.elision) {
5713           if (!state.inES5()) {
5714             warning("W070");
5715           } else {
5716             warning("W128");
5717             do {
5718               advance(",");
5719             } while (state.tokens.next.id === ",");
5720             continue;
5721           }
5722         }
5723         advance(",");
5724       }
5725 
5726       if (state.tokens.next.id === "]") {
5727         break;
5728       }
5729 
5730       this.first.push(expression(10));
5731       if (state.tokens.next.id === ",") {
5732         comma({ allowTrailing: true });
5733         if (state.tokens.next.id === "]" && !state.inES5()) {
5734           warning("W070", state.tokens.curr);
5735           break;
5736         }
5737       } else {
5738         break;
5739       }
5740     }
5741     if (b) {
5742       indent -= state.option.indent;
5743     }
5744     advance("]", this);
5745     return this;
5746   });

5749   function isMethod() {
5750     return state.funct["(statement)"] && state.funct["(statement)"].type === "class" ||
5751            state.funct["(context)"] && state.funct["(context)"]["(verb)"] === "class";
5752   }

5755   function isPropertyName(token) {
5756     return token.identifier || token.id === "(string)" || token.id === "(number)";
5757   }

5760   function propertyName(preserveOrToken) {
5761     var id;
5762     var preserve = true;
5763     if (typeof preserveOrToken === "object") {
5764       id = preserveOrToken;
5765     } else {
5766       preserve = preserveOrToken;
5767       id = optionalidentifier(false, true, preserve);
5768     }
5769 
5770     if (!id) {
5771       if (state.tokens.next.id === "(string)") {
5772         id = state.tokens.next.value;
5773         if (!preserve) {
5774           advance();
5775         }
5776       } else if (state.tokens.next.id === "(number)") {
5777         id = state.tokens.next.value.toString();
5778         if (!preserve) {
5779           advance();
5780         }
5781       }
5782     } else if (typeof id === "object") {
5783       if (id.id === "(string)" || id.id === "(identifier)") id = id.value;
5784       else if (id.id === "(number)") id = id.value.toString();
5785     }
5786 
5787     if (id === "hasOwnProperty") {
5788       warning("W001");
5789     }
5790 
5791     return id;
5792   }
5793   function functionparams(options) {
5794     var next;
5795     var paramsIds = [];
5796     var ident;
5797     var tokens = [];
5798     var t;
5799     var pastDefault = false;
5800     var pastRest = false;
5801     var arity = 0;
5802     var loneArg = options && options.loneArg;
5803 
5804     if (loneArg && loneArg.identifier === true) {
5805       state.funct["(scope)"].addParam(loneArg.value, loneArg);
5806       return { arity: 1, params: [ loneArg.value ] };
5807     }
5808 
5809     next = state.tokens.next;
5810 
5811     if (!options || !options.parsedOpening) {
5812       advance("(");
5813     }
5814 
5815     if (state.tokens.next.id === ")") {
5816       advance(")");
5817       return;
5818     }
5819 
5820     function addParam(addParamArgs) {
5821       state.funct["(scope)"].addParam.apply(state.funct["(scope)"], addParamArgs);
5822     }
5823 
5824     for (;;) {
5825       arity++;
5826       var currentParams = [];
5827 
5828       if (_.contains(["{", "["], state.tokens.next.id)) {
5829         tokens = destructuringPattern();
5830         for (t in tokens) {
5831           t = tokens[t];
5832           if (t.id) {
5833             paramsIds.push(t.id);
5834             currentParams.push([t.id, t.token]);
5835           }
5836         }
5837       } else {
5838         if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "...")) pastRest = true;
5839         ident = identifier(true);
5840         if (ident) {
5841           paramsIds.push(ident);
5842           currentParams.push([ident, state.tokens.curr]);
5843         } else {
5844           while (!checkPunctuators(state.tokens.next, [",", ")"])) advance();
5845         }
5846       }
5847       if (pastDefault) {
5848         if (state.tokens.next.id !== "=") {
5849           error("W138", state.tokens.current);
5850         }
5851       }
5852       if (state.tokens.next.id === "=") {
5853         if (!state.inES6()) {
5854           warning("W119", state.tokens.next, "default parameters", "6");
5855         }
5856         advance("=");
5857         pastDefault = true;
5858         expression(10);
5859       }
5860       currentParams.forEach(addParam);
5861 
5862       if (state.tokens.next.id === ",") {
5863         if (pastRest) {
5864           warning("W131", state.tokens.next);
5865         }
5866         comma();
5867       } else {
5868         advance(")", next);
5869         return { arity: arity, params: paramsIds };
5870       }
5871     }
5872   }

5874   function functor(name, token, overwrites) {
5875     var funct = {
5876       "(name)"      : name,
5877       "(breakage)"  : 0,
5878       "(loopage)"   : 0,
5879       "(tokens)"    : {},
5880       "(properties)": {},
5881 
5882       "(catch)"     : false,
5883       "(global)"    : false,
5884 
5885       "(line)"      : null,
5886       "(character)" : null,
5887       "(metrics)"   : null,
5888       "(statement)" : null,
5889       "(context)"   : null,
5890       "(scope)"     : null,
5891       "(comparray)" : null,
5892       "(generator)" : null,
5893       "(arrow)"     : null,
5894       "(params)"    : null
5895     };
5896 
5897     if (token) {
5898       _.extend(funct, {
5899         "(line)"     : token.line,
5900         "(character)": token.character,
5901         "(metrics)"  : createMetrics(token)
5902       });
5903     }
5904 
5905     _.extend(funct, overwrites);
5906 
5907     if (funct["(context)"]) {
5908       funct["(scope)"] = funct["(context)"]["(scope)"];
5909       funct["(comparray)"]  = funct["(context)"]["(comparray)"];
5910     }
5911 
5912     return funct;
5913   }

5915   function isFunctor(token) {
5916     return "(scope)" in token;
5917   }
5918   function hasParsedCode(funct) {
5919     return funct["(global)"] && !funct["(verb)"];
5920   }

5922   function doTemplateLiteral(left) {
5923     var ctx = this.context;
5924     var noSubst = this.noSubst;
5925     var depth = this.depth;
5926 
5927     if (!noSubst) {
5928       while (!end()) {
5929         if (!state.tokens.next.template || state.tokens.next.depth > depth) {
5930           expression(0); // should probably have different rbp?
5931         } else {
5932           advance();
5933         }
5934       }
5935     }
5936 
5937     return {
5938       id: "(template)",
5939       type: "(template)",
5940       tag: left
5941     };
5942 
5943     function end() {
5944       if (state.tokens.curr.template && state.tokens.curr.tail &&
5945           state.tokens.curr.context === ctx) return true;
5946       var complete = (state.tokens.next.template && state.tokens.next.tail &&
5947                       state.tokens.next.context === ctx);
5948       if (complete) advance();
5949       return complete || state.tokens.next.isUnclosed;
5950     }
5951   }
5952   function doFunction(options) {
5953     var f, token, name, statement, classExprBinding, isGenerator, isArrow, ignoreLoopFunc;
5954     var oldOption = state.option;
5955     var oldIgnored = state.ignored;
5956 
5957     if (options) {
5958       name = options.name;
5959       statement = options.statement;
5960       classExprBinding = options.classExprBinding;
5961       isGenerator = options.type === "generator";
5962       isArrow = options.type === "arrow";
5963       ignoreLoopFunc = options.ignoreLoopFunc;
5964     }
5965 
5966     state.option = Object.create(state.option);
5967     state.ignored = Object.create(state.ignored);
5968 
5969     state.funct = functor(name || state.nameStack.infer(), state.tokens.next, {
5970       "(statement)": statement,
5971       "(context)":   state.funct,
5972       "(arrow)":     isArrow,
5973       "(generator)": isGenerator
5974     });
5975 
5976     f = state.funct;
5977     token = state.tokens.curr;
5978     token.funct = state.funct;
5979 
5980     functions.push(state.funct);
5981     state.funct["(scope)"].stack("functionouter");
5982     var internallyAccessibleName = name || classExprBinding;
5983     if (internallyAccessibleName) {
5984       state.funct["(scope)"].block.add(internallyAccessibleName,
5985         classExprBinding ? "class" : "function", state.tokens.curr, false);
5986     }
5987     state.funct["(scope)"].stack("functionparams");
5988 
5989     var paramsInfo = functionparams(options);
5990 
5991     if (paramsInfo) {
5992       state.funct["(params)"] = paramsInfo.params;
5993       state.funct["(metrics)"].arity = paramsInfo.arity;
5994       state.funct["(metrics)"].verifyMaxParametersPerFunction();
5995     } else {
5996       state.funct["(metrics)"].arity = 0;
5997     }
5998 
5999     if (isArrow) {
6000       if (!state.inES6(true)) {
6001         warning("W119", state.tokens.curr, "arrow function syntax (=>)", "6");
6002       }
6003 
6004       if (!options.loneArg) {
6005         advance("=>");
6006       }
6007     }
6008 
6009     block(false, true, true, isArrow);
6010 
6011     if (!state.option.noyield && isGenerator &&
6012         state.funct["(generator)"] !== "yielded") {
6013       warning("W124", state.tokens.curr);
6014     }
6015 
6016     state.funct["(metrics)"].verifyMaxStatementsPerFunction();
6017     state.funct["(metrics)"].verifyMaxComplexityPerFunction();
6018     state.funct["(unusedOption)"] = state.option.unused;
6019     state.option = oldOption;
6020     state.ignored = oldIgnored;
6021     state.funct["(last)"] = state.tokens.curr.line;
6022     state.funct["(lastcharacter)"] = state.tokens.curr.character;
6023     state.funct["(scope)"].unstack(); // also does usage and label checks
6024     state.funct["(scope)"].unstack();
6025 
6026     state.funct = state.funct["(context)"];
6027 
6028     if (!ignoreLoopFunc && !state.option.loopfunc && state.funct["(loopage)"]) {
6029       if (f["(isCapturing)"]) {
6030         warning("W083", token);
6031       }
6032     }
6033 
6034     return f;
6035   }

6037   function createMetrics(functionStartToken) {
6038     return {
6039       statementCount: 0,
6040       nestedBlockDepth: -1,
6041       ComplexityCount: 1,
6042       arity: 0,
6043 
6044       verifyMaxStatementsPerFunction: function() {
6045         if (state.option.maxstatements &&
6046           this.statementCount > state.option.maxstatements) {
6047           warning("W071", functionStartToken, this.statementCount);
6048         }
6049       },
6050 
6051       verifyMaxParametersPerFunction: function() {
6052         if (_.isNumber(state.option.maxparams) &&
6053           this.arity > state.option.maxparams) {
6054           warning("W072", functionStartToken, this.arity);
6055         }
6056       },
6057 
6058       verifyMaxNestedBlockDepthPerFunction: function() {
6059         if (state.option.maxdepth &&
6060           this.nestedBlockDepth > 0 &&
6061           this.nestedBlockDepth === state.option.maxdepth + 1) {
6062           warning("W073", null, this.nestedBlockDepth);
6063         }
6064       },
6065 
6066       verifyMaxComplexityPerFunction: function() {
6067         var max = state.option.maxcomplexity;
6068         var cc = this.ComplexityCount;
6069         if (max && cc > max) {
6070           warning("W074", functionStartToken, cc);
6071         }
6072       }
6073     };
6074   }
6075 
6076   function increaseComplexityCount() {
6077     state.funct["(metrics)"].ComplexityCount += 1;
6078   }
6079   function checkCondAssignment(expr) {
6080     var id, paren;
6081     if (expr) {
6082       id = expr.id;
6083       paren = expr.paren;
6084       if (id === "," && (expr = expr.exprs[expr.exprs.length - 1])) {
6085         id = expr.id;
6086         paren = paren || expr.paren;
6087       }
6088     }
6089     switch (id) {
6090     case "=":
6091     case "+=":
6092     case "-=":
6093     case "*=":
6094     case "%=":
6095     case "&=":
6096     case "|=":
6097     case "^=":
6098     case "/=":
6099       if (!paren && !state.option.boss) {
6100         warning("W084");
6101       }
6102     }
6103   }
6104   function checkProperties(props) {
6105     if (state.inES5()) {
6106       for (var name in props) {
6107         if (props[name] && props[name].setterToken && !props[name].getterToken) {
6108           warning("W078", props[name].setterToken);
6109         }
6110       }
6111     }
6112   }

6114   function metaProperty(name, c) {
6115     if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, ".")) {
6116       var left = state.tokens.curr.id;
6117       advance(".");
6118       var id = identifier();
6119       state.tokens.curr.isMetaProperty = true;
6120       if (name !== id) {
6121         error("E057", state.tokens.prev, left, id);
6122       } else {
6123         c();
6124       }
6125       return state.tokens.curr;
6126     }
6127   }

6129   (function(x) {
6130     x.nud = function() {
6131       var b, f, i, p, t, isGeneratorMethod = false, nextVal;
6132       var props = Object.create(null); // All properties, including accessors
6133 
6134       b = state.tokens.curr.line !== startLine(state.tokens.next);
6135       if (b) {
6136         indent += state.option.indent;
6137         if (state.tokens.next.from === indent + state.option.indent) {
6138           indent += state.option.indent;
6139         }
6140       }
6141 
6142       var blocktype = lookupBlockType();
6143       if (blocktype.isDestAssign) {
6144         this.destructAssign = destructuringPattern({ openingParsed: true, assignment: true });
6145         return this;
6146       }
6147 
6148       for (;;) {
6149         if (state.tokens.next.id === "}") {
6150           break;
6151         }
6152 
6153         nextVal = state.tokens.next.value;
6154         if (state.tokens.next.identifier &&
6155             (peekIgnoreEOL().id === "," || peekIgnoreEOL().id === "}")) {
6156           if (!state.inES6()) {
6157             warning("W104", state.tokens.next, "object short notation", "6");
6158           }
6159           i = propertyName(true);
6160           saveProperty(props, i, state.tokens.next);
6161 
6162           expression(10);
6163 
6164         } else if (peek().id !== ":" && (nextVal === "get" || nextVal === "set")) {
6165           advance(nextVal);
6166 
6167           if (!state.inES5()) {
6168             error("E034");
6169           }
6170 
6171           i = propertyName();
6172           if (!i && !state.inES6()) {
6173             error("E035");
6174           }
6175           if (i) {
6176             saveAccessor(nextVal, props, i, state.tokens.curr);
6177           }
6178 
6179           t = state.tokens.next;
6180           f = doFunction();
6181           p = f["(params)"];
6182           if (nextVal === "get" && i && p) {
6183             warning("W076", t, p[0], i);
6184           } else if (nextVal === "set" && i && (!p || p.length !== 1)) {
6185             warning("W077", t, i);
6186           }
6187         } else {
6188           if (state.tokens.next.value === "*" && state.tokens.next.type === "(punctuator)") {
6189             if (!state.inES6()) {
6190               warning("W104", state.tokens.next, "generator functions", "6");
6191             }
6192             advance("*");
6193             isGeneratorMethod = true;
6194           } else {
6195             isGeneratorMethod = false;
6196           }
6197 
6198           if (state.tokens.next.id === "[") {
6199             i = computedPropertyName();
6200             state.nameStack.set(i);
6201           } else {
6202             state.nameStack.set(state.tokens.next);
6203             i = propertyName();
6204             saveProperty(props, i, state.tokens.next);
6205 
6206             if (typeof i !== "string") {
6207               break;
6208             }
6209           }
6210 
6211           if (state.tokens.next.value === "(") {
6212             if (!state.inES6()) {
6213               warning("W104", state.tokens.curr, "concise methods", "6");
6214             }
6215             doFunction({ type: isGeneratorMethod ? "generator" : null });
6216           } else {
6217             advance(":");
6218             expression(10);
6219           }
6220         }
6221 
6222         countMember(i);
6223 
6224         if (state.tokens.next.id === ",") {
6225           comma({ allowTrailing: true, property: true });
6226           if (state.tokens.next.id === ",") {
6227             warning("W070", state.tokens.curr);
6228           } else if (state.tokens.next.id === "}" && !state.inES5()) {
6229             warning("W070", state.tokens.curr);
6230           }
6231         } else {
6232           break;
6233         }
6234       }
6235       if (b) {
6236         indent -= state.option.indent;
6237       }
6238       advance("}", this);
6239 
6240       checkProperties(props);
6241 
6242       return this;
6243     };
6244     x.fud = function() {
6245       error("E036", state.tokens.curr);
6246     };
6247   }(delim("{")));

6249   function destructuringPattern(options) {
6250     var isAssignment = options && options.assignment;
6251 
6252     if (!state.inES6()) {
6253       warning("W104", state.tokens.curr,
6254         isAssignment ? "destructuring assignment" : "destructuring binding", "6");
6255     }
6256 
6257     return destructuringPatternRecursive(options);
6258   }
6259 
6260   function destructuringPatternRecursive(options) {
6261     var ids;
6262     var identifiers = [];
6263     var openingParsed = options && options.openingParsed;
6264     var isAssignment = options && options.assignment;
6265     var recursiveOptions = isAssignment ? { assignment: isAssignment } : null;
6266     var firstToken = openingParsed ? state.tokens.curr : state.tokens.next;
6267 
6268     var nextInnerDE = function() {
6269       var ident;
6270       if (checkPunctuators(state.tokens.next, ["[", "{"])) {
6271         ids = destructuringPatternRecursive(recursiveOptions);
6272         for (var id in ids) {
6273           id = ids[id];
6274           identifiers.push({ id: id.id, token: id.token });
6275         }
6276       } else if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, ",")) {
6277         identifiers.push({ id: null, token: state.tokens.curr });
6278       } else if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "(")) {
6279         advance("(");
6280         nextInnerDE();
6281         advance(")");
6282       } else {
6283         var is_rest = checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "...");
6284 
6285         if (isAssignment) {
6286           var identifierToken = is_rest ? peek(0) : state.tokens.next;
6287           if (!identifierToken.identifier) {
6288             warning("E030", identifierToken, identifierToken.value);
6289           }
6290           var assignTarget = expression(155);
6291           if (assignTarget) {
6292             checkLeftSideAssign(assignTarget);
6293             if (assignTarget.identifier) {
6294               ident = assignTarget.value;
6295             }
6296           }
6297         } else {
6298           ident = identifier();
6299         }
6300         if (ident) {
6301           identifiers.push({ id: ident, token: state.tokens.curr });
6302         }
6303         return is_rest;
6304       }
6305       return false;
6306     };
6307     var assignmentProperty = function() {
6308       var id;
6309       if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "[")) {
6310         advance("[");
6311         expression(10);
6312         advance("]");
6313         advance(":");
6314         nextInnerDE();
6315       } else if (state.tokens.next.id === "(string)" ||
6316                  state.tokens.next.id === "(number)") {
6317         advance();
6318         advance(":");
6319         nextInnerDE();
6320       } else {
6321         id = identifier();
6322         if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, ":")) {
6323           advance(":");
6324           nextInnerDE();
6325         } else if (id) {
6326           if (isAssignment) {
6327             checkLeftSideAssign(state.tokens.curr);
6328           }
6329           identifiers.push({ id: id, token: state.tokens.curr });
6330         }
6331       }
6332     };
6333     if (checkPunctuator(firstToken, "[")) {
6334       if (!openingParsed) {
6335         advance("[");
6336       }
6337       if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "]")) {
6338         warning("W137", state.tokens.curr);
6339       }
6340       var element_after_rest = false;
6341       while (!checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "]")) {
6342         if (nextInnerDE() && !element_after_rest &&
6343             checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, ",")) {
6344           warning("W130", state.tokens.next);
6345           element_after_rest = true;
6346         }
6347         if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "=")) {
6348           if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.prev, "...")) {
6349             advance("]");
6350           } else {
6351             advance("=");
6352           }
6353           if (state.tokens.next.id === "undefined") {
6354             warning("W080", state.tokens.prev, state.tokens.prev.value);
6355           }
6356           expression(10);
6357         }
6358         if (!checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "]")) {
6359           advance(",");
6360         }
6361       }
6362       advance("]");
6363     } else if (checkPunctuator(firstToken, "{")) {
6364 
6365       if (!openingParsed) {
6366         advance("{");
6367       }
6368       if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "}")) {
6369         warning("W137", state.tokens.curr);
6370       }
6371       while (!checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "}")) {
6372         assignmentProperty();
6373         if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "=")) {
6374           advance("=");
6375           if (state.tokens.next.id === "undefined") {
6376             warning("W080", state.tokens.prev, state.tokens.prev.value);
6377           }
6378           expression(10);
6379         }
6380         if (!checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "}")) {
6381           advance(",");
6382           if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "}")) {
6383             break;
6384           }
6385         }
6386       }
6387       advance("}");
6388     }
6389     return identifiers;
6390   }
6391 
6392   function destructuringPatternMatch(tokens, value) {
6393     var first = value.first;
6394 
6395     if (!first)
6396       return;
6397 
6398     _.zip(tokens, Array.isArray(first) ? first : [ first ]).forEach(function(val) {
6399       var token = val[0];
6400       var value = val[1];
6401 
6402       if (token && value)
6403         token.first = value;
6404       else if (token && token.first && !value)
6405         warning("W080", token.first, token.first.value);
6406     });
6407   }
6408 
6409   function blockVariableStatement(type, statement, context) {
6410     var prefix = context && context.prefix;
6411     var inexport = context && context.inexport;
6412     var isLet = type === "let";
6413     var isConst = type === "const";
6414     var tokens, lone, value, letblock;
6415 
6416     if (!state.inES6()) {
6417       warning("W104", state.tokens.curr, type, "6");
6418     }
6419 
6420     if (isLet && state.tokens.next.value === "(") {
6421       if (!state.inMoz()) {
6422         warning("W118", state.tokens.next, "let block");
6423       }
6424       advance("(");
6425       state.funct["(scope)"].stack();
6426       letblock = true;
6427     } else if (state.funct["(noblockscopedvar)"]) {
6428       error("E048", state.tokens.curr, isConst ? "Const" : "Let");
6429     }
6430 
6431     statement.first = [];
6432     for (;;) {
6433       var names = [];
6434       if (_.contains(["{", "["], state.tokens.next.value)) {
6435         tokens = destructuringPattern();
6436         lone = false;
6437       } else {
6438         tokens = [ { id: identifier(), token: state.tokens.curr } ];
6439         lone = true;
6440       }
6441 
6442       if (!prefix && isConst && state.tokens.next.id !== "=") {
6443         warning("E012", state.tokens.curr, state.tokens.curr.value);
6444       }
6445 
6446       for (var t in tokens) {
6447         if (tokens.hasOwnProperty(t)) {
6448           t = tokens[t];
6449           if (state.funct["(scope)"].block.isGlobal()) {
6450             if (predefined[t.id] === false) {
6451               warning("W079", t.token, t.id);
6452             }
6453           }
6454           if (t.id && !state.funct["(noblockscopedvar)"]) {
6455             state.funct["(scope)"].addlabel(t.id, {
6456               type: type,
6457               token: t.token });
6458             names.push(t.token);
6459 
6460             if (lone && inexport) {
6461               state.funct["(scope)"].setExported(t.token.value, t.token);
6462             }
6463           }
6464         }
6465       }
6466 
6467       if (state.tokens.next.id === "=") {
6468         advance("=");
6469         if (!prefix && state.tokens.next.id === "undefined") {
6470           warning("W080", state.tokens.prev, state.tokens.prev.value);
6471         }
6472         if (!prefix && peek(0).id === "=" && state.tokens.next.identifier) {
6473           warning("W120", state.tokens.next, state.tokens.next.value);
6474         }
6475         value = expression(prefix ? 120 : 10);
6476         if (lone) {
6477           tokens[0].first = value;
6478         } else {
6479           destructuringPatternMatch(names, value);
6480         }
6481       }
6482 
6483       statement.first = statement.first.concat(names);
6484 
6485       if (state.tokens.next.id !== ",") {
6486         break;
6487       }
6488       comma();
6489     }
6490     if (letblock) {
6491       advance(")");
6492       block(true, true);
6493       statement.block = true;
6494       state.funct["(scope)"].unstack();
6495     }
6496 
6497     return statement;
6498   }
6499 
6500   var conststatement = stmt("const", function(context) {
6501     return blockVariableStatement("const", this, context);
6502   });
6503   conststatement.exps = true;
6504 
6505   var letstatement = stmt("let", function(context) {
6506     return blockVariableStatement("let", this, context);
6507   });
6508   letstatement.exps = true;

6510   var varstatement = stmt("var", function(context) {
6511     var prefix = context && context.prefix;
6512     var inexport = context && context.inexport;
6513     var tokens, lone, value;
6514     var implied = context && context.implied;
6515     var report = !(context && context.ignore);
6516 
6517     this.first = [];
6518     for (;;) {
6519       var names = [];
6520       if (_.contains(["{", "["], state.tokens.next.value)) {
6521         tokens = destructuringPattern();
6522         lone = false;
6523       } else {
6524         tokens = [ { id: identifier(), token: state.tokens.curr } ];
6525         lone = true;
6526       }
6527 
6528       if (!(prefix && implied) && report && state.option.varstmt) {
6529         warning("W132", this);
6530       }
6531 
6532       this.first = this.first.concat(names);
6533 
6534       for (var t in tokens) {
6535         if (tokens.hasOwnProperty(t)) {
6536           t = tokens[t];
6537           if (!implied && state.funct["(global)"]) {
6538             if (predefined[t.id] === false) {
6539               warning("W079", t.token, t.id);
6540             } else if (state.option.futurehostile === false) {
6541               if ((!state.inES5() && vars.ecmaIdentifiers[5][t.id] === false) ||
6542                 (!state.inES6() && vars.ecmaIdentifiers[6][t.id] === false)) {
6543                 warning("W129", t.token, t.id);
6544               }
6545             }
6546           }
6547           if (t.id) {
6548             if (implied === "for") {
6549 
6550               if (!state.funct["(scope)"].has(t.id)) {
6551                 if (report) warning("W088", t.token, t.id);
6552               }
6553               state.funct["(scope)"].block.use(t.id, t.token);
6554             } else {
6555               state.funct["(scope)"].addlabel(t.id, {
6556                 type: "var",
6557                 token: t.token });
6558 
6559               if (lone && inexport) {
6560                 state.funct["(scope)"].setExported(t.id, t.token);
6561               }
6562             }
6563             names.push(t.token);
6564           }
6565         }
6566       }
6567 
6568       if (state.tokens.next.id === "=") {
6569         state.nameStack.set(state.tokens.curr);
6570 
6571         advance("=");
6572         if (!prefix && report && !state.funct["(loopage)"] &&
6573           state.tokens.next.id === "undefined") {
6574           warning("W080", state.tokens.prev, state.tokens.prev.value);
6575         }
6576         if (peek(0).id === "=" && state.tokens.next.identifier) {
6577           if (!prefix && report &&
6578               !state.funct["(params)"] ||
6579               state.funct["(params)"].indexOf(state.tokens.next.value) === -1) {
6580             warning("W120", state.tokens.next, state.tokens.next.value);
6581           }
6582         }
6583         value = expression(prefix ? 120 : 10);
6584         if (lone) {
6585           tokens[0].first = value;
6586         } else {
6587           destructuringPatternMatch(names, value);
6588         }
6589       }
6590 
6591       if (state.tokens.next.id !== ",") {
6592         break;
6593       }
6594       comma();
6595     }
6596 
6597     return this;
6598   });
6599   varstatement.exps = true;

6601   blockstmt("class", function() {
6602     return classdef.call(this, true);
6603   });

6605   function classdef(isStatement) {
6606     if (!state.inES6()) {
6607       warning("W104", state.tokens.curr, "class", "6");
6608     }
6609     if (isStatement) {
6610       this.name = identifier();
6611 
6612       state.funct["(scope)"].addlabel(this.name, {
6613         type: "class",
6614         token: state.tokens.curr });
6615     } else if (state.tokens.next.identifier && state.tokens.next.value !== "extends") {
6616       this.name = identifier();
6617       this.namedExpr = true;
6618     } else {
6619       this.name = state.nameStack.infer();
6620     }
6621     classtail(this);
6622     return this;
6623   }
6624 
6625   function classtail(c) {
6626     var wasInClassBody = state.inClassBody;
6627     if (state.tokens.next.value === "extends") {
6628       advance("extends");
6629       c.heritage = expression(10);
6630     }
6631 
6632     state.inClassBody = true;
6633     advance("{");
6634     c.body = classbody(c);
6635     advance("}");
6636     state.inClassBody = wasInClassBody;
6637   }
6638 
6639   function classbody(c) {
6640     var name;
6641     var isStatic;
6642     var isGenerator;
6643     var getset;
6644     var props = Object.create(null);
6645     var staticProps = Object.create(null);
6646     var computed;
6647     for (var i = 0; state.tokens.next.id !== "}"; ++i) {
6648       name = state.tokens.next;
6649       isStatic = false;
6650       isGenerator = false;
6651       getset = null;
6652       if (name.id === ";") {
6653         warning("W032");
6654         advance(";");
6655         continue;
6656       }
6657 
6658       if (name.id === "*") {
6659         isGenerator = true;
6660         advance("*");
6661         name = state.tokens.next;
6662       }
6663       if (name.id === "[") {
6664         name = computedPropertyName();
6665         computed = true;
6666       } else if (isPropertyName(name)) {
6667         advance();
6668         computed = false;
6669         if (name.identifier && name.value === "static") {
6670           if (checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "*")) {
6671             isGenerator = true;
6672             advance("*");
6673           }
6674           if (isPropertyName(state.tokens.next) || state.tokens.next.id === "[") {
6675             computed = state.tokens.next.id === "[";
6676             isStatic = true;
6677             name = state.tokens.next;
6678             if (state.tokens.next.id === "[") {
6679               name = computedPropertyName();
6680             } else advance();
6681           }
6682         }
6683 
6684         if (name.identifier && (name.value === "get" || name.value === "set")) {
6685           if (isPropertyName(state.tokens.next) || state.tokens.next.id === "[") {
6686             computed = state.tokens.next.id === "[";
6687             getset = name;
6688             name = state.tokens.next;
6689             if (state.tokens.next.id === "[") {
6690               name = computedPropertyName();
6691             } else advance();
6692           }
6693         }
6694       } else {
6695         warning("W052", state.tokens.next, state.tokens.next.value || state.tokens.next.type);
6696         advance();
6697         continue;
6698       }
6699 
6700       if (!checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "(")) {
6701         error("E054", state.tokens.next, state.tokens.next.value);
6702         while (state.tokens.next.id !== "}" &&
6703                !checkPunctuator(state.tokens.next, "(")) {
6704           advance();
6705         }
6706         if (state.tokens.next.value !== "(") {
6707           doFunction({ statement: c });
6708         }
6709       }
6710 
6711       if (!computed) {
6712         if (getset) {
6713           saveAccessor(
6714             getset.value, isStatic ? staticProps : props, name.value, name, true, isStatic);
6715         } else {
6716           if (name.value === "constructor") {
6717             state.nameStack.set(c);
6718           } else {
6719             state.nameStack.set(name);
6720           }
6721           saveProperty(isStatic ? staticProps : props, name.value, name, true, isStatic);
6722         }
6723       }
6724 
6725       if (getset && name.value === "constructor") {
6726         var propDesc = getset.value === "get" ? "class getter method" : "class setter method";
6727         error("E049", name, propDesc, "constructor");
6728       } else if (name.value === "prototype") {
6729         error("E049", name, "class method", "prototype");
6730       }
6731 
6732       propertyName(name);
6733 
6734       doFunction({
6735         statement: c,
6736         type: isGenerator ? "generator" : null,
6737         classExprBinding: c.namedExpr ? c.name : null
6738       });
6739     }
6740 
6741     checkProperties(props);
6742   }

6744   blockstmt("function", function(context) {
6745     var inexport = context && context.inexport;
6746     var generator = false;
6747     if (state.tokens.next.value === "*") {
6748       advance("*");
6749       if (state.inES6({ strict: true })) {
6750         generator = true;
6751       } else {
6752         warning("W119", state.tokens.curr, "function*", "6");
6753       }
6754     }
6755     if (inblock) {
6756       warning("W082", state.tokens.curr);
6757     }
6758     var i = optionalidentifier();
6759 
6760     state.funct["(scope)"].addlabel(i, {
6761       type: "function",
6762       token: state.tokens.curr });
6763 
6764     if (i === undefined) {
6765       warning("W025");
6766     } else if (inexport) {
6767       state.funct["(scope)"].setExported(i, state.tokens.prev);
6768     }
6769 
6770     doFunction({
6771       name: i,
6772       statement: this,
6773       type: generator ? "generator" : null,
6774       ignoreLoopFunc: inblock // a declaration may already have warned
6775     });
6776     if (state.tokens.next.id === "(" && state.tokens.next.line === state.tokens.curr.line) {
6777       error("E039");
6778     }
6779     return this;
6780   });

6782   prefix("function", function() {

6786       if (!state.inES6()) {
6787         warning("W119", state.tokens.curr, "function*", "6");
6788       }
6789       advance("*");

6798   blockstmt("if", function() {
6799     var t = state.tokens.next;
6800     increaseComplexityCount();
6801     state.condition = true;
6802     advance("(");
6803     var expr = expression(0);
6804     checkCondAssignment(expr);
6805     var forinifcheck = null;
6806     if (state.option.forin && state.forinifcheckneeded) {
6807       state.forinifcheckneeded = false; // We only need to analyze the first if inside the loop
6808       forinifcheck = state.forinifchecks[state.forinifchecks.length - 1];
6809       if (expr.type === "(punctuator)" && expr.value === "!") {
6810         forinifcheck.type = "(negative)";
6811       } else {
6812         forinifcheck.type = "(positive)";
6813       }
6814     }
6815 
6816     advance(")", t);
6817     state.condition = false;
6818     var s = block(true, true);
6819     if (forinifcheck && forinifcheck.type === "(negative)") {
6820       if (s && s[0] && s[0].type === "(identifier)" && s[0].value === "continue") {
6821         forinifcheck.type = "(negative-with-continue)";
6822       }
6823     }
6824 
6825     if (state.tokens.next.id === "else") {
6826       advance("else");
6827       if (state.tokens.next.id === "if" || state.tokens.next.id === "switch") {
6828         statement();
6829       } else {
6830         block(true, true);
6831       }
6832     }
6833     return this;
6834   });

6836   blockstmt("try", function() {
6837     var b;
6838 
6839     function doCatch() {
6840       advance("catch");
6841       advance("(");
6842 
6843       state.funct["(scope)"].stack("catchparams");
6844 
6845       if (checkPunctuators(state.tokens.next, ["[", "{"])) {
6846         var tokens = destructuringPattern();
6847         _.each(tokens, function(token) {
6848           if (token.id) {
6849             state.funct["(scope)"].addParam(token.id, token, "exception");
6850           }
6851         });
6852       } else if (state.tokens.next.type !== "(identifier)") {
6853         warning("E030", state.tokens.next, state.tokens.next.value);
6854       } else {
6855         state.funct["(scope)"].addParam(identifier(), state.tokens.curr, "exception");
6856       }
6857 
6858       if (state.tokens.next.value === "if") {
6859         if (!state.inMoz()) {
6860           warning("W118", state.tokens.curr, "catch filter");
6861         }
6862         advance("if");
6863         expression(0);
6864       }
6865 
6866       advance(")");
6867 
6868       block(false);
6869 
6870       state.funct["(scope)"].unstack();
6871     }
6872 
6873     block(true);
6874 
6875     while (state.tokens.next.id === "catch") {
6876       increaseComplexityCount();
6877       if (b && (!state.inMoz())) {
6878         warning("W118", state.tokens.next, "multiple catch blocks");
6879       }
6880       doCatch();
6881       b = true;
6882     }
6883 
6884     if (state.tokens.next.id === "finally") {
6885       advance("finally");
6886       block(true);
6887       return;
6888     }
6889 
6890     if (!b) {
6891       error("E021", state.tokens.next, "catch", state.tokens.next.value);
6892     }
6893 
6894     return this;
6895   });

6899     state.funct["(breakage)"] += 1;
6900     state.funct["(loopage)"] += 1;
6901     increaseComplexityCount();
6902     advance("(");
6903     checkCondAssignment(expression(0));
6904     advance(")", t);
6905     block(true, true);
6906     state.funct["(breakage)"] -= 1;
6907     state.funct["(loopage)"] -= 1;
6908     return this;
6909   }).labelled = true;

6911   blockstmt("with", function() {
6912     var t = state.tokens.next;
6913     if (state.isStrict()) {
6914       error("E010", state.tokens.curr);
6915     } else if (!state.option.withstmt) {
6916       warning("W085", state.tokens.curr);
6917     }
6918 
6919     advance("(");
6920     expression(0);
6921     advance(")", t);
6922     block(true, true);
6923 
6924     return this;
6925   });
