6927   blockstmt("switch", function() {
6928     var t = state.tokens.next;
6929     var g = false;
6930     var noindent = false;
6931 
6932     state.funct["(breakage)"] += 1;
6933     advance("(");
6934     checkCondAssignment(expression(0));
6935     advance(")", t);
6936     t = state.tokens.next;
6937     advance("{");
6938 
6939     if (state.tokens.next.from === indent)
6940       noindent = true;
6941 
6942     if (!noindent)
6943       indent += state.option.indent;
6944 
6945     this.cases = [];
6946 
6947     for (;;) {
6948       switch (state.tokens.next.id) {
6949       case "case":
6950         switch (state.funct["(verb)"]) {
6951         case "yield":
6952         case "break":
6953         case "case":
6954         case "continue":
6955         case "return":
6956         case "switch":
6957         case "throw":
6958           break;
6959         default:
6960           if (!state.tokens.curr.caseFallsThrough) {
6961             warning("W086", state.tokens.curr, "case");
6962           }
6963         }
6964 
6965         advance("case");
6966         this.cases.push(expression(0));
6967         increaseComplexityCount();
6968         g = true;
6969         advance(":");
6970         state.funct["(verb)"] = "case";
6971         break;
6972       case "default":
6973         switch (state.funct["(verb)"]) {
6974         case "yield":
6975         case "break":
6976         case "continue":
6977         case "return":
6978         case "throw":
6979           break;
6980         default:
6981           if (this.cases.length) {
6982             if (!state.tokens.curr.caseFallsThrough) {
6983               warning("W086", state.tokens.curr, "default");
6984             }
6985           }
6986         }
6987 
6988         advance("default");
6989         g = true;
6990         advance(":");
6991         break;
6992       case "}":
6993         if (!noindent)
6994           indent -= state.option.indent;
6995 
6996         advance("}", t);
6997         state.funct["(breakage)"] -= 1;
6998         state.funct["(verb)"] = undefined;
6999         return;
7000       case "(end)":
7001         error("E023", state.tokens.next, "}");
7002         return;
7003       default:
7004         indent += state.option.indent;
7005         if (g) {
7006           switch (state.tokens.curr.id) {
7007           case ",":
7008             error("E040");
7009             return;
7010           case ":":
7011             g = false;
7012             statements();
7013             break;
7014           default:
7015             error("E025", state.tokens.curr);
7016             return;
7017           }
7018         } else {
7019           if (state.tokens.curr.id === ":") {
7020             advance(":");
7021             error("E024", state.tokens.curr, ":");
7022             statements();
7023           } else {
7024             error("E021", state.tokens.next, "case", state.tokens.next.value);
7025             return;
7026           }
7027         }
7028         indent -= state.option.indent;
7029       }
7030     }
7031     return this;
7032   }).labelled = true;
7033 
7034   stmt("debugger", function() {
7035     if (!state.option.debug) {
7036       warning("W087", this);
7037     }
7038     return this;
7039   }).exps = true;
7040 
7041   (function() {
7042     var x = stmt("do", function() {
7043       state.funct["(breakage)"] += 1;
7044       state.funct["(loopage)"] += 1;
7045       increaseComplexityCount();
7046 
7047       this.first = block(true, true);
7048       advance("while");
7049       var t = state.tokens.next;
7050       advance("(");

7553   var lookupBlockType = function() {
7554     var pn, pn1, prev;
7555     var i = -1;
7556     var bracketStack = 0;
7557     var ret = {};
7558     if (checkPunctuators(state.tokens.curr, ["[", "{"])) {
7559       bracketStack += 1;
7560     }
7561     do {
7562       prev = i === -1 ? state.tokens.curr : pn;
7563       pn = i === -1 ? state.tokens.next : peek(i);
7564       pn1 = peek(i + 1);
7565       i = i + 1;
7566       if (checkPunctuators(pn, ["[", "{"])) {
7567         bracketStack += 1;
7568       } else if (checkPunctuators(pn, ["]", "}"])) {
7569         bracketStack -= 1;
7570       }
7571       if (bracketStack === 1 && pn.identifier && pn.value === "for" &&
7572           !checkPunctuator(prev, ".")) {
7573         ret.isCompArray = true;
7574         ret.notJson = true;
7575         break;
7576       }
7577       if (bracketStack === 0 && checkPunctuators(pn, ["}", "]"])) {
7578         if (pn1.value === "=") {
7579           ret.isDestAssign = true;
7580           ret.notJson = true;
7581           break;
7582         } else if (pn1.value === ".") {
7583           ret.notJson = true;
7584           break;
7585         }
7586       }
7587       if (checkPunctuator(pn, ";")) {
7588         ret.isBlock = true;
7589         ret.notJson = true;
7590       }
7591     } while (bracketStack > 0 && pn.id !== "(end)");
7592     return ret;
7593   };

7595   function saveProperty(props, name, tkn, isClass, isStatic) {
7596     var msg = ["key", "class method", "static class method"];
7597     msg = msg[(isClass || false) + (isStatic || false)];
7598     if (tkn.identifier) {
7599       name = tkn.value;
7600     }
7601 
7602     if (props[name] && name !== "__proto__") {
7603       warning("W075", state.tokens.next, msg, name);
7604     } else {
7605       props[name] = Object.create(null);
7606     }
7607 
7608     props[name].basic = true;
7609     props[name].basictkn = tkn;
7610   }
7611   function saveAccessor(accessorType, props, name, tkn, isClass, isStatic) {
7612     var flagName = accessorType === "get" ? "getterToken" : "setterToken";
7613     var msg = "";
7614 
7615     if (isClass) {
7616       if (isStatic) {
7617         msg += "static ";
7618       }
7619       msg += accessorType + "ter method";
7620     } else {
7621       msg = "key";
7622     }
7623 
7624     state.tokens.curr.accessorType = accessorType;
7625     state.nameStack.set(tkn);
7626 
7627     if (props[name]) {
7628       if ((props[name].basic || props[name][flagName]) && name !== "__proto__") {
7629         warning("W075", state.tokens.next, msg, name);
7630       }
7631     } else {
7632       props[name] = Object.create(null);
7633     }
7634 
7635     props[name][flagName] = tkn;
7636   }

7647   function checkPunctuators(token, values) {
7648     if (token.type === "(punctuator)") {
7649       return _.contains(values, token.value);
7650     }
7651     return false;
7652   }
7653   function checkPunctuator(token, value) {
7654     return token.type === "(punctuator)" && token.value === value;
7655   }
7656   function destructuringAssignOrJsonValue() {
7657     var block = lookupBlockType();
7658     if (block.notJson) {
7659       if (!state.inES6() && block.isDestAssign) {
7660         warning("W104", state.tokens.curr, "destructuring assignment", "6");
7661       }
7662       statements();
7663     } else {
7664       state.option.laxbreak = true;
7665       state.jsonMode = true;
7666       jsonValue();
7667     }
7668   }
7669   var arrayComprehension = function() {
7670     var CompArray = function() {
7671       this.mode = "use";
7672       this.variables = [];
7673     };
7674     var _carrays = [];
7675     var _current;
7676     function declare(v) {
7677       var l = _current.variables.filter(function(elt) {
7678         if (elt.value === v) {
7679           elt.undef = false;
7680           return v;
7681         }
7682       }).length;
7683       return l !== 0;
7684     }
7685     function use(v) {
7686       var l = _current.variables.filter(function(elt) {
7687         if (elt.value === v && !elt.undef) {
7688           if (elt.unused === true) {
7689             elt.unused = false;
7690           }
7691           return v;
7692         }
7693       }).length;
7694       return (l === 0);
7695     }
7696     return { stack: function() {
7697           _current = new CompArray();
7698           _carrays.push(_current);
7699         },
7700         unstack: function() {
7701           _current.variables.filter(function(v) {
7702             if (v.unused)
7703               warning("W098", v.token, v.raw_text || v.value);
7704             if (v.undef)
7705               state.funct["(scope)"].block.use(v.value, v.token);
7706           });
7707           _carrays.splice(-1, 1);

7713         },

7744             if (use(v)) {

8236 function Lexer(source) {

8241       .replace(/\r\n/g, "\n")

8246     if (lines[0].indexOf("node") !== -1) {

8326   scanPunctuator: function() {
8327     var ch1 = this.peek();
8328     var ch2, ch3, ch4;
8329 
8330     switch (ch1) {
8331     case ".":
8332       if ((/^[0-9]$/).test(this.peek(1))) {
8333         return null;
8334       }
8335       if (this.peek(1) === "." && this.peek(2) === ".") {
8336         return {
8337           type: Token.Punctuator,
8338           value: "..."
8339         };
8340       }
8341     case "(":
8342     case ")":
8343     case ";":
8344     case ",":
8345     case "[":
8346     case "]":
8347     case ":":
8348     case "~":
8349     case "?":

8351         type: Token.Punctuator,
8352         value: ch1
8353       };
8354     case "{":

8357         type: Token.Punctuator,
8358         value: ch1

8361       if (this.inContext(Context.Block)) {

8363       }

8365         type: Token.Punctuator,
8366         value: ch1
8367       };
8368     case "#":
8369       return {
8370         type: Token.Punctuator,
8371         value: ch1
8372       };
8373     case "":
8374       return null;
8375     }
8376     ch2 = this.peek(1);
8377     ch3 = this.peek(2);
8378     ch4 = this.peek(3);
8379     if (ch1 === ">" && ch2 === ">" && ch3 === ">" && ch4 === "=") {
8380       return {
8381         type: Token.Punctuator,
8382         value: ">>>="
8383       };
8384     }
8385     if (ch1 === "=" && ch2 === "=" && ch3 === "=") {
8386       return {
8387         type: Token.Punctuator,
8388         value: "==="
8389       };
8390     }
8391 
8392     if (ch1 === "!" && ch2 === "=" && ch3 === "=") {
8393       return {
8394         type: Token.Punctuator,
8395         value: "!=="
8396       };
8397     }
8398

8400       return {

8402         value: ">>>"
8403       };

8405 
8406     if (ch1 === "<" && ch2 === "<" && ch3 === "=") {
8407       return {
8408         type: Token.Punctuator,
8409         value: "<<="

8411     }
8412

8414       return {
8415         type: Token.Punctuator,
8416         value: ">>="
8417       };
8418     }
8419     if (ch1 === "=" && ch2 === ">") {
8420       return {

8425     if (ch1 === ch2 && ("+-<>&|".indexOf(ch1) >= 0)) {
8426       return {
8427         type: Token.Punctuator,
8428         value: ch1 + ch2
8429       };
8430     }
8431 
8432     if ("<>=!+-*%&|^".indexOf(ch1) >= 0) {
8433       if (ch2 === "=") {
8434         return {
8435           type: Token.Punctuator,
8436           value: ch1 + ch2
8437         };
8438       }
8439 
8440       return {
8441         type: Token.Punctuator,
8442         value: ch1
8443       };
8444     }
8445     if (ch1 === "/") {
8446       if (ch2 === "=") {
8447         return {
8448           type: Token.Punctuator,
8449           value: "/="
8450         };
8451       }
8452 
8453       return {
8454         type: Token.Punctuator,
8455         value: "/"
8456       };
8457     }
8458 
8459     return null;
8460   },
8461   scanComments: function() {
8462     var ch1 = this.peek();
8463     var ch2 = this.peek(1);
8464     var rest = this.input.substr(2);
8465     var startLine = this.line;
8466     var startChar = this.char;
8467     var self = this;
8468     function commentToken(label, body, opt) {
8469       var special = ["jshint", "jslint", "members", "member", "globals", "global", "exported"];
8470       var isSpecial = false;
8471       var value = label + body;
8472       var commentType = "plain";
8473       opt = opt || {};
8474 
8475       if (opt.isMultiline) {
8476         value += "*/";
8477       }
8478 
8479       body = body.replace(/\n/g, " ");
8480 
8481       if (label === "/*" && reg.fallsThrough.test(body)) {
8482         isSpecial = true;
8483         commentType = "falls through";
8484       }
8485 
8486       special.forEach(function(str) {
8487         if (isSpecial) {
8488           return;
8489         }
8490         if (label === "//" && str !== "jshint") {
8491           return;
8492         }
8493 
8494         if (body.charAt(str.length) === " " && body.substr(0, str.length) === str) {
8495           isSpecial = true;
8496           label = label + str;
8497           body = body.substr(str.length);
8498         }
8499 
8500         if (!isSpecial && body.charAt(0) === " " && body.charAt(str.length + 1) === " " &&
8501           body.substr(1, str.length) === str) {
8502           isSpecial = true;
8503           label = label + " " + str;
8504           body = body.substr(str.length + 1);
8505         }
8506 
8507         if (!isSpecial) {
8508           return;
8509         }
8510 
8511         switch (str) {
8512         case "member":
8513           commentType = "members";
8514           break;
8515         case "global":
8516           commentType = "globals";
8517           break;
8518         default:
8519           var options = body.split(":").map(function(v) {
8520             return v.replace(/^\s+/, "").replace(/\s+$/, "");
8521           });
8522 
8523           if (options.length === 2) {
8524             switch (options[0]) {
8525             case "ignore":
8526               switch (options[1]) {
8527               case "start":
8528                 self.ignoringLinterErrors = true;
8529                 isSpecial = false;
8530                 break;
8531               case "end":
8532                 self.ignoringLinterErrors = false;
8533                 isSpecial = false;
8534                 break;
8535               }
8536             }
8537           }
8538 
8539           commentType = str;
8540         }
8541       });
8542 
8543       return {
8544         type: Token.Comment,
8545         commentType: commentType,
8546         value: value,
8547         body: body,
8548         isSpecial: isSpecial,
8549         isMultiline: opt.isMultiline || false,
8550         isMalformed: opt.isMalformed || false
8551       };
8552     }
8553     if (ch1 === "*" && ch2 === "/") {
8554       this.trigger("error", {
8555         code: "E018",
8556         line: startLine,
8557         character: startChar
8558       });
8559 
8560       this.skip(2);
8561       return null;
8562     }
8563     if (ch1 !== "/" || (ch2 !== "*" && ch2 !== "/")) {
8564       return null;
8565     }
8566     if (ch2 === "/") {
8567       this.skip(this.input.length); // Skip to the EOL.
8568       return commentToken("//", rest);
8569     }
8570 
8571     var body = "";
8572     if (ch2 === "*") {
8573       this.inComment = true;
8574       this.skip(2);
8575 
8576       while (this.peek() !== "*" || this.peek(1) !== "/") {
8577         if (this.peek() === "") { // End of Line
8578           body += "\n";
8579           if (!this.nextLine()) {
8580             this.trigger("error", {
8581               code: "E017",
8582               line: startLine,
8583               character: startChar
8584             });
8585 
8586             this.inComment = false;
8587             return commentToken("/*", body, {
8588               isMultiline: true,
8589               isMalformed: true
8590             });
8591           }
8592         } else {
8593           body += this.peek();
8594           this.skip();
8595         }
8596       }
8597 
8598       this.skip(2);
8599       this.inComment = false;
8600       return commentToken("/*", body, { isMultiline: true });
8601     }
8602   },
8603   scanKeyword: function() {
8604     var result = /^[a-zA-Z_$][a-zA-Z0-9_$]*/.exec(this.input);
8605     var keywords = [
8606       "if", "in", "do", "var", "for", "new",
8607       "try", "let", "this", "else", "case",
8608       "void", "with", "enum", "while", "break",
8609       "catch", "throw", "const", "yield", "class",
8610       "super", "return", "typeof", "delete",
8611       "switch", "export", "import", "default",
8612       "finally", "extends", "function", "continue",
8613       "debugger", "instanceof"
8614     ];
8615 
8616     if (result && keywords.indexOf(result[0]) >= 0) {
8617       return {
8618         type: Token.Keyword,
8619         value: result[0]
8620       };
8621     }
8622 
8623     return null;
8624   },
8625   scanIdentifier: function() {
8626     var id = "";
8627     var index = 0;
8628     var type, char;
8629 
8630     function isNonAsciiIdentifierStart(code) {
8631       return code > 256;
8632     }
8633 
8634     function isNonAsciiIdentifierPart(code) {
8635       return code > 256;
8636     }
8637 
8638     function isHexDigit(str) {
8639       return (/^[0-9a-fA-F]$/).test(str);
8640     }
8641 
8642     var readUnicodeEscapeSequence = function() {
8643       index += 1;
8644 
8645       if (this.peek(index) !== "u") {
8646         return null;
8647       }
8648 
8649       var ch1 = this.peek(index + 1);
8650       var ch2 = this.peek(index + 2);
8651       var ch3 = this.peek(index + 3);
8652       var ch4 = this.peek(index + 4);
8653       var code;
8654 
8655       if (isHexDigit(ch1) && isHexDigit(ch2) && isHexDigit(ch3) && isHexDigit(ch4)) {
8656         code = parseInt(ch1 + ch2 + ch3 + ch4, 16);
8657 
8658         if (asciiIdentifierPartTable[code] || isNonAsciiIdentifierPart(code)) {
8659           index += 5;
8660           return "\\u" + ch1 + ch2 + ch3 + ch4;
8661         }
8662 
8663         return null;
8664       }
8665 
8666       return null;
8667     }.bind(this);
8668 
8669     var getIdentifierStart = function() {
8670       var chr = this.peek(index);
8671       var code = chr.charCodeAt(0);
8672 
8673       if (code === 92) {
8674         return readUnicodeEscapeSequence();
8675       }
8676 
8677       if (code < 128) {
8678         if (asciiIdentifierStartTable[code]) {
8679           index += 1;
8680           return chr;
8681         }
8682 
8683         return null;
8684       }
8685 
8686       if (isNonAsciiIdentifierStart(code)) {
8687         index += 1;
8688         return chr;
8689       }
8690 
8691       return null;
8692     }.bind(this);
8693 
8694     var getIdentifierPart = function() {
8695       var chr = this.peek(index);
8696       var code = chr.charCodeAt(0);
8697 
8698       if (code === 92) {
8699         return readUnicodeEscapeSequence();
8700       }
8701 
8702       if (code < 128) {
8703         if (asciiIdentifierPartTable[code]) {
8704           index += 1;
8705           return chr;
8706         }
8707 
8708         return null;
8709       }
8710 
8711       if (isNonAsciiIdentifierPart(code)) {
8712         index += 1;
8713         return chr;
8714       }
8715 
8716       return null;
8717     }.bind(this);
8718 
8719     function removeEscapeSequences(id) {
8720       return id.replace(/\\u([0-9a-fA-F]{4})/g, function(m0, codepoint) {
8721         return String.fromCharCode(parseInt(codepoint, 16));
8722       });
8723     }
8724 
8725     char = getIdentifierStart();
8726     if (char === null) {
8727       return null;
8728     }
8729 
8730     id = char;
8731     for (;;) {
8732       char = getIdentifierPart();
8733 
8734       if (char === null) {
8735         break;
8736       }
8737 
8738       id += char;
8739     }
8740 
8741     switch (id) {
8742     case "true":
8743     case "false":
8744       type = Token.BooleanLiteral;
8745       break;
8746     case "null":
8747       type = Token.NullLiteral;
8748       break;
8749     default:
8750       type = Token.Identifier;
8751     }
8752 
8753     return {
8754       type: type,
8755       value: removeEscapeSequences(id),
8756       text: id,
8757       tokenLength: id.length
8758     };
8759   },
8760   scanNumericLiteral: function() {
8761     var index = 0;
8762     var value = "";
8763     var length = this.input.length;
8764     var char = this.peek(index);
8765     var bad;
8766     var isAllowedDigit = isDecimalDigit;
8767     var base = 10;
8768     var isLegacy = false;
8769 
8770     function isDecimalDigit(str) {
8771       return (/^[0-9]$/).test(str);
8772     }
8773 
8774     function isOctalDigit(str) {
8775       return (/^[0-7]$/).test(str);
8776     }
8777 
8778     function isBinaryDigit(str) {
8779       return (/^[01]$/).test(str);
8780     }
8781 
8782     function isHexDigit(str) {
8783       return (/^[0-9a-fA-F]$/).test(str);
8784     }
8785 
8786     function isIdentifierStart(ch) {
8787       return (ch === "$") || (ch === "_") || (ch === "\\") ||
8788         (ch >= "a" && ch <= "z") || (ch >= "A" && ch <= "Z");
8789     }
8790     if (char !== "." && !isDecimalDigit(char)) {
8791       return null;
8792     }
8793 
8794     if (char !== ".") {
8795       value = this.peek(index);
8796       index += 1;
8797       char = this.peek(index);
8798 
8799       if (value === "0") {
8800         if (char === "x" || char === "X") {
8801           isAllowedDigit = isHexDigit;
8802           base = 16;
8803 
8804           index += 1;
8805           value += char;
8806         }
8807         if (char === "o" || char === "O") {
8808           isAllowedDigit = isOctalDigit;
8809           base = 8;
8810 
8811           if (!state.inES6(true)) {
8812             this.trigger("warning", {
8813               code: "W119",
8814               line: this.line,
8815               character: this.char,
8816               data: [ "Octal integer literal", "6" ]
8817             });
8818           }
8819 
8820           index += 1;
8821           value += char;
8822         }
8823         if (char === "b" || char === "B") {
8824           isAllowedDigit = isBinaryDigit;
8825           base = 2;
8826 
8827           if (!state.inES6(true)) {
8828             this.trigger("warning", {
8829               code: "W119",
8830               line: this.line,
8831               character: this.char,
8832               data: [ "Binary integer literal", "6" ]
8833             });
8834           }
8835 
8836           index += 1;
8837           value += char;
8838         }
8839         if (isOctalDigit(char)) {
8840           isAllowedDigit = isOctalDigit;
8841           base = 8;
8842           isLegacy = true;
8843           bad = false;
8844 
8845           index += 1;
8846           value += char;
8847         }
8848         if (!isOctalDigit(char) && isDecimalDigit(char)) {
8849           index += 1;
8850           value += char;
8851         }
8852       }
8853 
8854       while (index < length) {
8855         char = this.peek(index);
8856 
8857         if (isLegacy && isDecimalDigit(char)) {
8858           bad = true;
8859         } else if (!isAllowedDigit(char)) {
8860           break;
8861         }
8862         value += char;
8863         index += 1;
8864       }
8865 
8866       if (isAllowedDigit !== isDecimalDigit) {
8867         if (!isLegacy && value.length <= 2) { // 0x
8868           return {
8869             type: Token.NumericLiteral,
8870             value: value,
8871             isMalformed: true
8872           };
8873         }
8874 
8875         if (index < length) {
8876           char = this.peek(index);
8877           if (isIdentifierStart(char)) {
8878             return null;
8879           }
8880         }
8881 
8882         return {
8883           type: Token.NumericLiteral,
8884           value: value,
8885           base: base,
8886           isLegacy: isLegacy,
8887           isMalformed: false
8888         };
8889       }
8890     }
8891     if (char === ".") {
8892       value += char;
8893       index += 1;
8894 
8895       while (index < length) {
8896         char = this.peek(index);
8897         if (!isDecimalDigit(char)) {
8898           break;
8899         }
8900         value += char;
8901         index += 1;
8902       }
8903     }
8904     if (char === "e" || char === "E") {
8905       value += char;
8906       index += 1;
8907       char = this.peek(index);
8908 
8909       if (char === "+" || char === "-") {
8910         value += this.peek(index);
8911         index += 1;
8912       }
8913 
8914       char = this.peek(index);
8915       if (isDecimalDigit(char)) {
8916         value += char;
8917         index += 1;
8918 
8919         while (index < length) {
8920           char = this.peek(index);
8921           if (!isDecimalDigit(char)) {
8922             break;
8923           }
8924           value += char;
8925           index += 1;
8926         }
8927       } else {
8928         return null;
8929       }
8930     }
8931 
8932     if (index < length) {
8933       char = this.peek(index);
8934       if (isIdentifierStart(char)) {
8935         return null;
8936       }
8937     }
8938 
8939     return {
8940       type: Token.NumericLiteral,
8941       value: value,
8942       base: base,
8943       isMalformed: !isFinite(value)
8944     };
8945   },
8946   scanEscapeSequence: function(checks) {
8947     var allowNewLine = false;
8948     var jump = 1;
8949     this.skip();
8950     var char = this.peek();
8951 
8952     switch (char) {
8953     case "'":
8954       this.triggerAsync("warning", {
8955         code: "W114",
8956         line: this.line,
8957         character: this.char,
8958         data: [ "\\'" ]
8959       }, checks, function() {return state.jsonMode; });
8960       break;
8961     case "b":
8962       char = "\\b";
8963       break;
8964     case "f":
8965       char = "\\f";
8966       break;
8967     case "n":
8968       char = "\\n";
8969       break;
8970     case "r":
8971       char = "\\r";
8972       break;
8973     case "t":
8974       char = "\\t";
8975       break;
8976     case "0":
8977       char = "\\0";
8978       var n = parseInt(this.peek(1), 10);
8979       this.triggerAsync("warning", {
8980         code: "W115",
8981         line: this.line,
8982         character: this.char
8983       }, checks,
8984       function() { return n >= 0 && n <= 7 && state.isStrict(); });
8985       break;
8986     case "u":
8987       var hexCode = this.input.substr(1, 4);
8988       var code = parseInt(hexCode, 16);
8989       if (isNaN(code)) {
8990         this.trigger("warning", {
8991           code: "W052",
8992           line: this.line,
8993           character: this.char,
8994           data: [ "u" + hexCode ]
8995         });
8996       }
8997       char = String.fromCharCode(code);
8998       jump = 5;
8999       break;
9000     case "v":
9001       this.triggerAsync("warning", {
9002         code: "W114",
9003         line: this.line,
9004         character: this.char,
9005         data: [ "\\v" ]
9006       }, checks, function() { return state.jsonMode; });
9007 
9008       char = "\v";
9009       break;
9010     case "x":
9011       var  x = parseInt(this.input.substr(1, 2), 16);
9012 
9013       this.triggerAsync("warning", {
9014         code: "W114",
9015         line: this.line,
9016         character: this.char,
9017         data: [ "\\x-" ]
9018       }, checks, function() { return state.jsonMode; });
9019 
9020       char = String.fromCharCode(x);
9021       jump = 3;
9022       break;
9023     case "\\":
9024       char = "\\\\";
9025       break;
9026     case "\"":
9027       char = "\\\"";
9028       break;
9029     case "/":
9030       break;
9031     case "":
9032       allowNewLine = true;
9033       char = "";
9034       break;
9035     }
9036 
9037     return { char: char, jump: jump, allowNewLine: allowNewLine };
9038   },
9039   scanTemplateLiteral: function(checks) {
9040     var tokenType;
9041     var value = "";
9042     var ch;
9043     var startLine = this.line;
9044     var startChar = this.char;
9045     var depth = this.templateStarts.length;
9046 
9047     if (!state.inES6(true)) {
9048       return null;
9049     } else if (this.peek() === "`") {
9050       tokenType = Token.TemplateHead;
9051       this.templateStarts.push({ line: this.line, char: this.char });
9052       depth = this.templateStarts.length;
9053       this.skip(1);
9054       this.pushContext(Context.Template);
9055     } else if (this.inContext(Context.Template) && this.peek() === "}") {
9056       tokenType = Token.TemplateMiddle;
9057     } else {
9058       return null;
9059     }
9060 
9061     while (this.peek() !== "`") {
9062       while ((ch = this.peek()) === "") {
9063         value += "\n";
9064         if (!this.nextLine()) {
9065           var startPos = this.templateStarts.pop();
9066           this.trigger("error", {
9067             code: "E052",
9068             line: startPos.line,
9069             character: startPos.char
9070           });
9071           return {
9072             type: tokenType,
9073             value: value,
9074             startLine: startLine,
9075             startChar: startChar,
9076             isUnclosed: true,
9077             depth: depth,
9078             context: this.popContext()
9079           };
9080         }
9081       }
9082 
9083       if (ch === '$' && this.peek(1) === '{') {
9084         value += '${';
9085         this.skip(2);
9086         return {
9087           type: tokenType,
9088           value: value,
9089           startLine: startLine,
9090           startChar: startChar,
9091           isUnclosed: false,
9092           depth: depth,
9093           context: this.currentContext()
9094         };
9095       } else if (ch === '\\') {
9096         var escape = this.scanEscapeSequence(checks);
9097         value += escape.char;
9098         this.skip(escape.jump);
9099       } else if (ch !== '`') {
9100         value += ch;
9101         this.skip(1);
9102       }
9103     }
9104     tokenType = tokenType === Token.TemplateHead ? Token.NoSubstTemplate : Token.TemplateTail;
9105     this.skip(1);
9106     this.templateStarts.pop();
9107 
9108     return {
9109       type: tokenType,
9110       value: value,
9111       startLine: startLine,
9112       startChar: startChar,
9113       isUnclosed: false,
9114       depth: depth,
9115       context: this.popContext()
9116     };
9117   },
9118   scanStringLiteral: function(checks) {
9119     var quote = this.peek();
9120     if (quote !== "\"" && quote !== "'") {
9121       return null;
9122     }
9123     this.triggerAsync("warning", {
9124       code: "W108",
9125       line: this.line,
9126       character: this.char // +1?
9127     }, checks, function() { return state.jsonMode && quote !== "\""; });
9128 
9129     var value = "";
9130     var startLine = this.line;
9131     var startChar = this.char;
9132     var allowNewLine = false;
9133 
9134     this.skip();
9135 
9136     while (this.peek() !== quote) {
9137       if (this.peek() === "") { // End Of Line
9138         //
9139         if (!allowNewLine) {
9140           this.trigger("warning", {
9141             code: "W112",
9142             line: this.line,
9143             character: this.char
9144           });
9145         } else {
9146           allowNewLine = false;
9147           this.triggerAsync("warning", {
9148             code: "W043",
9149             line: this.line,
9150             character: this.char
9151           }, checks, function() { return !state.option.multistr; });
9152 
9153           this.triggerAsync("warning", {
9154             code: "W042",
9155             line: this.line,
9156             character: this.char
9157           }, checks, function() { return state.jsonMode && state.option.multistr; });
9158         }
9159         if (!this.nextLine()) {
9160           this.trigger("error", {
9161             code: "E029",
9162             line: startLine,
9163             character: startChar
9164           });
9165 
9166           return {
9167             type: Token.StringLiteral,
9168             value: value,
9169             startLine: startLine,
9170             startChar: startChar,
9171             isUnclosed: true,
9172             quote: quote
9173           };
9174         }
9175 
9176       } else { // Any character other than End Of Line
9177 
9178         allowNewLine = false;
9179         var char = this.peek();
9180         var jump = 1; // A length of a jump, after we're done
9181         if (char < " ") {
9182           this.trigger("warning", {
9183             code: "W113",
9184             line: this.line,
9185             character: this.char,
9186             data: [ "<non-printable>" ]
9187           });
9188         }
9189         if (char === "\\") {
9190           var parsed = this.scanEscapeSequence(checks);
9191           char = parsed.char;
9192           jump = parsed.jump;
9193           allowNewLine = parsed.allowNewLine;
9194         }
9195 
9196         value += char;
9197         this.skip(jump);
9198       }
9199     }
9200 
9201     this.skip();
9202     return {
9203       type: Token.StringLiteral,
9204       value: value,
9205       startLine: startLine,
9206       startChar: startChar,
9207       isUnclosed: false,
9208       quote: quote
9209     };
9210   },
9211   scanRegExp: function() {
9212     var index = 0;
9213     var length = this.input.length;
9214     var char = this.peek();
9215     var value = char;
9216     var body = "";
9217     var flags = [];
9218     var malformed = false;
9219     var isCharSet = false;
9220     var terminated;
9221 
9222     var scanUnexpectedChars = function() {
9223       if (char < " ") {
9224         malformed = true;
9225         this.trigger("warning", {
9226           code: "W048",
9227           line: this.line,
9228           character: this.char
9229         });
9230       }
9231       if (char === "<") {
9232         malformed = true;
9233         this.trigger("warning", {
9234           code: "W049",
9235           line: this.line,
9236           character: this.char,
9237           data: [ char ]
9238         });
9239       }
9240     }.bind(this);
9241     if (!this.prereg || char !== "/") {
9242       return null;
9243     }
9244 
9245     index += 1;
9246     terminated = false;
9247     while (index < length) {
9248       char = this.peek(index);
9249       value += char;
9250       body += char;
9251 
9252       if (isCharSet) {
9253         if (char === "]") {
9254           if (this.peek(index - 1) !== "\\" || this.peek(index - 2) === "\\") {
9255             isCharSet = false;
9256           }
9257         }
9258 
9259         if (char === "\\") {
9260           index += 1;
9261           char = this.peek(index);
9262           body += char;
9263           value += char;
9264 
9265           scanUnexpectedChars();
9266         }
9267 
9268         index += 1;
9269         continue;
9270       }
9271 
9272       if (char === "\\") {
9273         index += 1;
9274         char = this.peek(index);
9275         body += char;
9276         value += char;
9277 
9278         scanUnexpectedChars();
9279 
9280         if (char === "/") {
9281           index += 1;
9282           continue;
9283         }
9284 
9285         if (char === "[") {
9286           index += 1;
9287           continue;
9288         }
9289       }
9290 
9291       if (char === "[") {
9292         isCharSet = true;
9293         index += 1;
9294         continue;
9295       }
9296 
9297       if (char === "/") {
9298         body = body.substr(0, body.length - 1);
9299         terminated = true;
9300         index += 1;
9301         break;
9302       }
9303 
9304       index += 1;
9305     }
9306     if (!terminated) {
9307       this.trigger("error", {
9308         code: "E015",
9309         line: this.line,
9310         character: this.from
9311       });
9312 
9313       return void this.trigger("fatal", {
9314         line: this.line,
9315         from: this.from
9316       });
9317     }
9318     while (index < length) {
9319       char = this.peek(index);
9320       if (!/[gim]/.test(char)) {
9321         break;
9322       }
9323       flags.push(char);
9324       value += char;
9325       index += 1;
9326     }
9327     try {
9328       new RegExp(body, flags.join(""));
9329     } catch (err) {
9330       malformed = true;
9331       this.trigger("error", {
9332         code: "E016",
9333         line: this.line,
9334         character: this.char,
9335         data: [ err.message ] // Platform dependent!
9336       });
9337     }
9338 
9339     return {
9340       type: Token.RegExp,
9341       value: value,
9342       flags: flags,
9343       isMalformed: malformed
9344     };
9345   },
9346   scanNonBreakingSpaces: function() {
9347     return state.option.nonbsp ?
9348       this.input.search(/(\u00A0)/) : -1;
9349   },
9350   scanUnsafeChars: function() {
9351     return this.input.search(reg.unsafeChars);
9352   },
9353   next: function(checks) {
9354     this.from = this.char;
9355     var start;
9356     if (/\s/.test(this.peek())) {
9357       start = this.char;
9358 
9359       while (/\s/.test(this.peek())) {
9360         this.from += 1;
9361         this.skip();
9362       }
9363     }
9364     var match = this.scanComments() ||
9365       this.scanStringLiteral(checks) ||
9366       this.scanTemplateLiteral(checks);
9367 
9368     if (match) {
9369       return match;
9370     }
9371     match =
9372       this.scanRegExp() ||
9373       this.scanPunctuator() ||
9374       this.scanKeyword() ||
9375       this.scanIdentifier() ||
9376       this.scanNumericLiteral();
9377 
9378     if (match) {
9379       this.skip(match.tokenLength || match.value.length);
9380       return match;
9381     }
9382     return null;
9383   },
9384   nextLine: function() {
9385     var char;
9386 
9387     if (this.line >= this.getLines().length) {
9388       return false;
9389     }
9390 
9391     this.input = this.getLines()[this.line];
9392     this.line += 1;
9393     this.char = 1;
9394     this.from = 1;
9395 
9396     var inputTrimmed = this.input.trim();
9397 
9398     var startsWith = function() {
9399       return _.some(arguments, function(prefix) {
9400         return inputTrimmed.indexOf(prefix) === 0;
9401       });
9402     };
9403 
9404     var endsWith = function() {
9405       return _.some(arguments, function(suffix) {
9406         return inputTrimmed.indexOf(suffix, inputTrimmed.length - suffix.length) !== -1;
9407       });
9408     };
9409     if (this.ignoringLinterErrors === true) {
9410       if (!startsWith("/*", "//") && !(this.inComment && endsWith("*/"))) {
9411         this.input = "";
9412       }
9413     }
9414 
9415     char = this.scanNonBreakingSpaces();
9416     if (char >= 0) {
9417       this.trigger("warning", { code: "W125", line: this.line, character: char + 1 });
9418     }
9419 
9420     this.input = this.input.replace(/\t/g, state.tab);
9421     char = this.scanUnsafeChars();
9422 
9423     if (char >= 0) {
9424       this.trigger("warning", { code: "W100", line: this.line, character: char });
9425     }
9426     if (!this.ignoringLinterErrors && state.option.maxlen &&
9427       state.option.maxlen < this.input.length) {
9428       var inComment = this.inComment ||
9429         startsWith.call(inputTrimmed, "//") ||
9430         startsWith.call(inputTrimmed, "/*");
9431 
9432       var shouldTriggerError = !inComment || !reg.maxlenException.test(inputTrimmed);
9433 
9434       if (shouldTriggerError) {
9435         this.trigger("warning", { code: "W101", line: this.line, character: this.input.length });
9436       }
9437     }
9438 
9439     return true;
9440   },
9441   start: function() {
9442     this.nextLine();
9443   },
9444   token: function() {
9445     var checks = asyncTrigger();
9446     var token;
9447 
9448 
9449     function isReserved(token, isProperty) {
9450       if (!token.reserved) {
9451         return false;
9452       }
9453       var meta = token.meta;
9454 
9455       if (meta && meta.isFutureReservedWord && state.inES5()) {
9456         if (!meta.es5) {
9457           return false;
9458         }
9459         if (meta.strictOnly) {
9460           if (!state.option.strict && !state.isStrict()) {
9461             return false;
9462           }
9463         }
9464 
9465         if (isProperty) {
9466           return false;
9467         }
9468       }
9469 
9470       return true;
9471     }
9472     var create = function(type, value, isProperty, token) {
9473       var obj;
9474 
9475       if (type !== "(endline)" && type !== "(end)") {
9476         this.prereg = false;
9477       }
9478 
9479       if (type === "(punctuator)") {
9480         switch (value) {
9481         case ".":
9482         case ")":
9483         case "~":
9484         case "#":
9485         case "]":
9486         case "++":
9487         case "--":
9488           this.prereg = false;
9489           break;
9490         default:
9491           this.prereg = true;
9492         }
9493 
9494         obj = Object.create(state.syntax[value] || state.syntax["(error)"]);
9495       }
9496 
9497       if (type === "(identifier)") {
9498         if (value === "return" || value === "case" || value === "typeof") {
9499           this.prereg = true;
9500         }
9501 
9502         if (_.has(state.syntax, value)) {
9503           obj = Object.create(state.syntax[value] || state.syntax["(error)"]);
9504           if (!isReserved(obj, isProperty && type === "(identifier)")) {
9505             obj = null;
9506           }
9507         }
9508       }
9509 
9510       if (!obj) {
9511         obj = Object.create(state.syntax[type]);
9512       }
9513 
9514       obj.identifier = (type === "(identifier)");
9515       obj.type = obj.type || type;
9516       obj.value = value;
9517       obj.line = this.line;
9518       obj.character = this.char;
9519       obj.from = this.from;
9520       if (obj.identifier && token) obj.raw_text = token.text || token.value;
9521       if (token && token.startLine && token.startLine !== this.line) {
9522         obj.startLine = token.startLine;
9523       }
9524       if (token && token.context) {
9525         obj.context = token.context;
9526       }
9527       if (token && token.depth) {
9528         obj.depth = token.depth;
9529       }
9530       if (token && token.isUnclosed) {
9531         obj.isUnclosed = token.isUnclosed;
9532       }
9533 
9534       if (isProperty && obj.identifier) {
9535         obj.isProperty = isProperty;
9536       }
9537 
9538       obj.check = checks.check;
9539 
9540       return obj;
9541     }.bind(this);
9542 
9543     for (;;) {
9544       if (!this.input.length) {
9545         if (this.nextLine()) {
9546           return create("(endline)", "");
9547         }
9548 
9549         if (this.exhausted) {
9550           return null;
9551         }
9552 
9553         this.exhausted = true;
9554         return create("(end)", "");
9555       }
9556 
9557       token = this.next(checks);
9558 
9559       if (!token) {
9560         if (this.input.length) {
9561           this.trigger("error", {
9562             code: "E024",
9563             line: this.line,
9564             character: this.char,
9565             data: [ this.peek() ]
9566           });
9567 
9568           this.input = "";
9569         }
9570 
9571         continue;
9572       }
9573 
9574       switch (token.type) {
9575       case Token.StringLiteral:
9576         this.triggerAsync("String", {
9577           line: this.line,
9578           char: this.char,
9579           from: this.from,
9580           startLine: token.startLine,
9581           startChar: token.startChar,
9582           value: token.value,
9583           quote: token.quote
9584         }, checks, function() { return true; });
9585 
9586         return create("(string)", token.value, null, token);
9587 
9588       case Token.TemplateHead:
9589         this.trigger("TemplateHead", {
9590           line: this.line,
9591           char: this.char,
9592           from: this.from,
9593           startLine: token.startLine,
9594           startChar: token.startChar,
9595           value: token.value
9596         });
9597         return create("(template)", token.value, null, token);
9598 
9599       case Token.TemplateMiddle:
9600         this.trigger("TemplateMiddle", {
9601           line: this.line,
9602           char: this.char,
9603           from: this.from,
9604           startLine: token.startLine,
9605           startChar: token.startChar,
9606           value: token.value
9607         });
9608         return create("(template middle)", token.value, null, token);
9609 
9610       case Token.TemplateTail:
9611         this.trigger("TemplateTail", {
9612           line: this.line,
9613           char: this.char,
9614           from: this.from,
9615           startLine: token.startLine,
9616           startChar: token.startChar,
9617           value: token.value
9618         });
9619         return create("(template tail)", token.value, null, token);
9620 
9621       case Token.NoSubstTemplate:
9622         this.trigger("NoSubstTemplate", {
9623           line: this.line,
9624           char: this.char,
9625           from: this.from,
9626           startLine: token.startLine,
9627           startChar: token.startChar,
9628           value: token.value
9629         });
9630         return create("(no subst template)", token.value, null, token);
9631 
9632       case Token.Identifier:
9633         this.triggerAsync("Identifier", {
9634           line: this.line,
9635           char: this.char,
9636           from: this.form,
9637           name: token.value,
9638           raw_name: token.text,
9639           isProperty: state.tokens.curr.id === "."
9640         }, checks, function() { return true; });
9641       case Token.Keyword:
9642       case Token.NullLiteral:
9643       case Token.BooleanLiteral:
9644         return create("(identifier)", token.value, state.tokens.curr.id === ".", token);
9645 
9646       case Token.NumericLiteral:
9647         if (token.isMalformed) {
9648           this.trigger("warning", {
9649             code: "W045",
9650             line: this.line,
9651             character: this.char,
9652             data: [ token.value ]
9653           });
9654         }
9655 
9656         this.triggerAsync("warning", {
9657           code: "W114",
9658           line: this.line,
9659           character: this.char,
9660           data: [ "0x-" ]
9661         }, checks, function() { return token.base === 16 && state.jsonMode; });
9662 
9663         this.triggerAsync("warning", {
9664           code: "W115",
9665           line: this.line,
9666           character: this.char
9667         }, checks, function() {
9668           return state.isStrict() && token.base === 8 && token.isLegacy;
9669         });
9670 
9671         this.trigger("Number", {
9672           line: this.line,
9673           char: this.char,
9674           from: this.from,
9675           value: token.value,
9676           base: token.base,
9677           isMalformed: token.malformed
9678         });
9679 
9680         return create("(number)", token.value);
9681 
9682       case Token.RegExp:
9683         return create("(regexp)", token.value);
9684 
9685       case Token.Comment:
9686         state.tokens.curr.comment = true;
9687 
9688         if (token.isSpecial) {
9689           return {
9690             id: '(comment)',
9691             value: token.value,
9692             body: token.body,
9693             type: token.commentType,
9694             isSpecial: token.isSpecial,
9695             line: this.line,
9696             character: this.char,
9697             from: this.from
9698           };
9699         }
9700 
9701         break;
9702 
9703       case "":
9704         break;
9705 
9706       default:
9707         return create("(punctuator)", token.value);
9708       }
9709     }
9710   }
9711 };

9714 exports.Context = Context;

9973   var type;
9974   if (!nameToken || nameToken.type === "class") {
9975     nameToken = this._stack[this.length - 2];

9989     prefix = nameToken.accessorType + " ";
9990   }

11664 define("ace/mode/javascript_worker",[], function(require, exports, module) {
11665 "use strict";
11666 
11667 var oop = require("../lib/oop");
11668 var Mirror = require("../worker/mirror").Mirror;
11669 var lint = require("./javascript/jshint").JSHINT;
11670 
11671 function startRegex(arr) {
11672     return RegExp("^(" + arr.join("|") + ")");
11673 }
11674 
11675 var disabledWarningsRe = startRegex([
11676     "Bad for in variable '(.+)'.",
11677     'Missing "use strict"'
11678 ]);
11679 var errorsRe = startRegex([
11680     "Unexpected",
11681     "Expected ",
11682     "Confusing (plus|minus)",
11683     "\\{a\\} unterminated regular expression",
11684     "Unclosed ",
11685     "Unmatched ",
11686     "Unbegun comment",
11687     "Bad invocation",
11688     "Missing space after",
11689     "Missing operator at"
11690 ]);
11691 var infoRe = startRegex([
11692     "Expected an assignment",
11693     "Bad escapement of EOL",
11694     "Unexpected comma",
11695     "Unexpected space",
11696     "Missing radix parameter.",
11697     "A leading decimal point can",
11698     "\\['{a}'\\] is better written in dot notation.",
11699     "'{a}' used out of scope"
11700 ]);
11701 
11702 var JavaScriptWorker = exports.JavaScriptWorker = function(sender) {
11703     Mirror.call(this, sender);
11704     this.setTimeout(500);
11705     this.setOptions();
11706 };
11707 
11708 oop.inherits(JavaScriptWorker, Mirror);
11709 
11710 (function() {
11711     this.setOptions = function(options) {
11712         this.options = options || {
11713             esnext: true,
11714             moz: true,
11715             devel: true,
11716             browser: true,
11717             node: true,
11718             laxcomma: true,
11719             laxbreak: true,
11720             lastsemic: true,
11721             onevar: false,
11722             passfail: false,
11723             maxerr: 100,
11724             expr: true,
11725             multistr: true,
11726             globalstrict: true
11727         };
11728         this.doc.getValue() && this.deferredUpdate.schedule(100);
11729     };
11730 
11731     this.changeOptions = function(newOptions) {
11732         oop.mixin(this.options, newOptions);
11733         this.doc.getValue() && this.deferredUpdate.schedule(100);
11734     };
11735 
11736     this.isValidJS = function(str) {
11737         try {
11738             eval("throw 0;" + str);
11739         } catch(e) {
11740             if (e === 0)
11741                 return true;
11742         }
11743         return false;
11744     };
11745 
11746     this.onUpdate = function() {
11747         var value = this.doc.getValue();
11748         value = value.replace(/^#!.*\n/, "\n");
11749         if (!value)
11750             return this.sender.emit("annotate", []);
11751 
11752         var errors = [];
11753         var maxErrorLevel = this.isValidJS(value) ? "warning" : "error";
11754         lint(value, this.options, this.options.globals);
11755         var results = lint.errors;
11756 
11757         var errorAdded = false;
11758         for (var i = 0; i < results.length; i++) {
11759             var error = results[i];
11760             if (!error)
11761                 continue;
11762             var raw = error.raw;
11763             var type = "warning";
11764 
11765             if (raw == "Missing semicolon.") {
11766                 var str = error.evidence.substr(error.character);
11767                 str = str.charAt(str.search(/\S/));
11768                 if (maxErrorLevel == "error" && str && /[\w\d{(['"]/.test(str)) {
11769                     error.reason = 'Missing ";" before statement';
11770                     type = "error";
11771                 } else {
11772                     type = "info";
11773                 }
11774             }
11775             else if (disabledWarningsRe.test(raw)) {
11776                 continue;
11777             }
11778             else if (infoRe.test(raw)) {
11779                 type = "info";
11780             }
11781             else if (errorsRe.test(raw)) {
11782                 errorAdded  = true;
11783                 type = maxErrorLevel;
11784             }
11785             else if (raw == "'{a}' is not defined.") {
11786                 type = "warning";
11787             }
11788             else if (raw == "'{a}' is defined but never used.") {
11789                 type = "info";
11790             }
11791 
11792             errors.push({
11793                 row: error.line-1,
11794                 column: error.character-1,
11795                 text: error.reason,
11796                 type: type,
11797                 raw: raw
11798             });
11799 
11800             if (errorAdded) {
11801             }
11802         }
11803         this.sender.emit("annotate", errors);
11804     };
11805 
11806 }).call(JavaScriptWorker.prototype);
11807 
11808 });

11810 define("ace/lib/es5-shim",[], function(require, exports, module) {
11811 
11812 //
11813 //
11814 function Empty() {}
11815 
11816 if (!Function.prototype.bind) {
11817     Function.prototype.bind = function bind(that) { // .length is 1
11818         var target = this;
11819         if (typeof target != "function") {
11820             throw new TypeError("Function.prototype.bind called on incompatible " + target);
11821         }
11822         var args = slice.call(arguments, 1); // for normal call
11823         var bound = function () {
11824 
11825             if (this instanceof bound) {
11826                 var result = target.apply(
11827                     this,
11828                     args.concat(slice.call(arguments))
11829                 );
11830                 if (Object(result) === result) {
11831                     return result;
11832                 }
11833                 return this;
11834 
11835             } else {
11836                 return target.apply(
11837                     that,
11838                     args.concat(slice.call(arguments))
11839                 );
11840 
11841             }
11842 
11843         };
11844         if(target.prototype) {
11845             Empty.prototype = target.prototype;
11846             bound.prototype = new Empty();
11847             Empty.prototype = null;
11848         }
11849         //
11850         return bound;
11851     };
11852 }
11853 var call = Function.prototype.call;
11854 var prototypeOfArray = Array.prototype;
11855 var prototypeOfObject = Object.prototype;
11856 var slice = prototypeOfArray.slice;
11857 var _toString = call.bind(prototypeOfObject.toString);
11858 var owns = call.bind(prototypeOfObject.hasOwnProperty);
11859 var defineGetter;
11860 var defineSetter;
11861 var lookupGetter;
11862 var lookupSetter;
11863 var supportsAccessors;
11864 if ((supportsAccessors = owns(prototypeOfObject, "__defineGetter__"))) {
11865     defineGetter = call.bind(prototypeOfObject.__defineGetter__);
11866     defineSetter = call.bind(prototypeOfObject.__defineSetter__);
11867     lookupGetter = call.bind(prototypeOfObject.__lookupGetter__);
11868     lookupSetter = call.bind(prototypeOfObject.__lookupSetter__);
11869 }
11870 
11871 //
11872 //
11873 if ([1,2].splice(0).length != 2) {
11874     if(function() { // test IE < 9 to splice bug - see issue #138
11875         function makeArray(l) {
11876             var a = new Array(l+2);
11877             a[0] = a[1] = 0;
11878             return a;
11879         }
11880         var array = [], lengthBefore;
11881         
11882         array.splice.apply(array, makeArray(20));
11883         array.splice.apply(array, makeArray(26));
11884 
11885         lengthBefore = array.length; //46
11886         array.splice(5, 0, "XXX"); // add one element
11887 
11888         lengthBefore + 1 == array.length
11889 
11890         if (lengthBefore + 1 == array.length) {
11891             return true;// has right splice implementation without bugs
11892         }
11893     }()) {//IE 6/7
11894         var array_splice = Array.prototype.splice;
11895         Array.prototype.splice = function(start, deleteCount) {
11896             if (!arguments.length) {
11897                 return [];
11898             } else {
11899                 return array_splice.apply(this, [
11900                     start === void 0 ? 0 : start,
11901                     deleteCount === void 0 ? (this.length - start) : deleteCount
11902                 ].concat(slice.call(arguments, 2)))
11903             }
11904         };
11905     } else {//IE8
11906         Array.prototype.splice = function(pos, removeCount){
11907             var length = this.length;
11908             if (pos > 0) {
11909                 if (pos > length)
11910                     pos = length;
11911             } else if (pos == void 0) {
11912                 pos = 0;
11913             } else if (pos < 0) {
11914                 pos = Math.max(length + pos, 0);
11915             }
11916 
11917             if (!(pos+removeCount < length))
11918                 removeCount = length - pos;
11919 
11920             var removed = this.slice(pos, pos+removeCount);
11921             var insert = slice.call(arguments, 2);
11922             var add = insert.length;            
11923             if (pos === length) {
11924                 if (add) {
11925                     this.push.apply(this, insert);
11926                 }
11927             } else {
11928                 var remove = Math.min(removeCount, length - pos);
11929                 var tailOldPos = pos + remove;
11930                 var tailNewPos = tailOldPos + add - remove;
11931                 var tailCount = length - tailOldPos;
11932                 var lengthAfterRemove = length - remove;
11933 
11934                 if (tailNewPos < tailOldPos) { // case A
11935                     for (var i = 0; i < tailCount; ++i) {
11936                         this[tailNewPos+i] = this[tailOldPos+i];
11937                     }
11938                 } else if (tailNewPos > tailOldPos) { // case B
11939                     for (i = tailCount; i--; ) {
11940                         this[tailNewPos+i] = this[tailOldPos+i];
11941                     }
11942                 } // else, add == remove (nothing to do)
11943 
11944                 if (add && pos === lengthAfterRemove) {
11945                     this.length = lengthAfterRemove; // truncate array
11946                     this.push.apply(this, insert);
11947                 } else {
11948                     this.length = lengthAfterRemove + add; // reserves space
11949                     for (i = 0; i < add; ++i) {
11950                         this[pos+i] = insert[i];
11951                     }
11952                 }
11953             }
11954             return removed;
11955         };
11956     }

12472 function toInteger(n) {
12473     n = +n;
12474     if (n !== n) { // isNaN
12475         n = 0;
12476     } else if (n !== 0 && n !== (1/0) && n !== -(1/0)) {
12477         n = (n > 0 || -1) * Math.floor(Math.abs(n));
12478     }
12479     return n;
12480 }

12482 function isPrimitive(input) {
12483     var type = typeof input;
12484     return (
12485         input === null ||
12486         type === "undefined" ||
12487         type === "boolean" ||
12488         type === "number" ||
12489         type === "string"
12490     );
12491 }
12492 
12493 function toPrimitive(input) {
12494     var val, valueOf, toString;
12495     if (isPrimitive(input)) {
12496         return input;
12497     }
12498     valueOf = input.valueOf;
12499     if (typeof valueOf === "function") {
12500         val = valueOf.call(input);
12501         if (isPrimitive(val)) {
12502             return val;
12503         }
12504     }
12505     toString = input.toString;
12506     if (typeof toString === "function") {
12507         val = toString.call(input);
12508         if (isPrimitive(val)) {
12509             return val;
12510         }
12511     }
12512     throw new TypeError();
12513 }
12514 var toObject = function (o) {
12515     if (o == null) { // this matches both null and undefined
12516         throw new TypeError("can't convert "+o+" to object");
12517     }
12518     return Object(o);
12519 };
